63/* Traits for a hash table for reusing already existing ipa_bits. */
64
65struct ipa_bit_ggc_hash_traits : public ggc_cache_remove <ipa_bits *>
66{
67 typedef ipa_bits *value_type;
68 typedef ipa_bits *compare_type;
69 static hashval_t
70 hash (const ipa_bits *p)
71 {
72 hashval_t t = (hashval_t) p->value.to_shwi ();
73 return iterative_hash_host_wide_int (p->mask.to_shwi (), t);
74 }
75 static bool
76 equal (const ipa_bits *a, const ipa_bits *b)
77 {
78 return a->value == b->value && a->mask == b->mask;
79 }
80 static void
81 mark_empty (ipa_bits *&p)
82 {
83 p = NULL;
84 }
85 static bool
86 is_empty (const ipa_bits *p)
87 {
88 return p == NULL;
89 }
90 static bool
91 is_deleted (const ipa_bits *p)
92 {
93 return p == reinterpret_cast<const ipa_bits *> (1);
94 }
95 static void
96 mark_deleted (ipa_bits *&p)
97 {
98 p = reinterpret_cast<ipa_bits *> (1);
99 }
100};
101
102/* Hash table for avoid repeated allocations of equal ipa_bits. */
103static GTY ((cache)) hash_table<ipa_bit_ggc_hash_traits> *ipa_bits_hash_table;

105/* Traits for a hash table for reusing value_ranges used for IPA. Note that
106 the equiv bitmap is not hashed and is expected to be NULL. */
107
108struct ipa_vr_ggc_hash_traits : public ggc_cache_remove <value_range *>
109{
110 typedef value_range *value_type;
111 typedef value_range *compare_type;
112 static hashval_t
113 hash (const value_range *p)
114 {
115 gcc_checking_assert (!p->equiv);
116 inchash::hash hstate (p->type);
117 hstate.add_ptr (p->min);
118 hstate.add_ptr (p->max);
119 return hstate.end ();
120 }
121 static bool
122 equal (const value_range *a, const value_range *b)
123 {
124 return a->type == b->type && a->min == b->min && a->max == b->max;
125 }
126 static void
127 mark_empty (value_range *&p)
128 {
129 p = NULL;
130 }
131 static bool
132 is_empty (const value_range *p)
133 {
134 return p == NULL;
135 }
136 static bool
137 is_deleted (const value_range *p)
138 {
139 return p == reinterpret_cast<const value_range *> (1);
140 }
141 static void
142 mark_deleted (value_range *&p)
143 {
144 p = reinterpret_cast<value_range *> (1);
145 }
146};
147
148/* Hash table for avoid repeated allocations of equal value_ranges. */
149static GTY ((cache)) hash_table<ipa_vr_ggc_hash_traits> *ipa_vr_hash_table;

173/* Return true if DECL_FUNCTION_SPECIFIC_OPTIMIZATION of the decl associated
174 with NODE should prevent us from analyzing it for the purposes of IPA-CP. */
175
176static bool
177ipa_func_spec_opts_forbid_analysis_p (struct cgraph_node *node)
178{
179 tree fs_opts = DECL_FUNCTION_SPECIFIC_OPTIMIZATION (node->decl);
180
181 if (!fs_opts)
182 return false;
183 return !opt_for_fn (node->decl, optimize) || !opt_for_fn (node->decl, flag_ipa_cp);
184}

186/* Return index of the formal whose tree is PTREE in function which corresponds
187 to INFO. */
188
189static int
190ipa_get_param_decl_index_1 (vec<ipa_param_descriptor, va_gc> *descriptors,
191 tree ptree)
192{
193 int i, count;
194
195 count = vec_safe_length (descriptors);
196 for (i = 0; i < count; i++)
197 if ((*descriptors)[i].decl_or_type == ptree)
198 return i;
199
200 return -1;
201}
202
203/* Return index of the formal whose tree is PTREE in function which corresponds
204 to INFO. */
205
206int
207ipa_get_param_decl_index (struct ipa_node_params *info, tree ptree)
208{
209 return ipa_get_param_decl_index_1 (info->descriptors, ptree);
210}

212/* Populate the param_decl field in parameter DESCRIPTORS that correspond to
213 NODE. */
214
215static void
216ipa_populate_param_decls (struct cgraph_node *node,
217 vec<ipa_param_descriptor, va_gc> &descriptors)
218{
219 tree fndecl;
220 tree fnargs;
221 tree parm;
222 int param_num;
223
224 fndecl = node->decl;
225 gcc_assert (gimple_has_body_p (fndecl));
226 fnargs = DECL_ARGUMENTS (fndecl);
227 param_num = 0;
228 for (parm = fnargs; parm; parm = DECL_CHAIN (parm))
229 {
230 descriptors[param_num].decl_or_type = parm;
231 descriptors[param_num].move_cost = estimate_move_cost (TREE_TYPE (parm),
232 true);
233 param_num++;
234 }
235}
236
237/* Return how many formal parameters FNDECL has. */
238
239int
240count_formal_params (tree fndecl)
241{
242 tree parm;
243 int count = 0;
244 gcc_assert (gimple_has_body_p (fndecl));
245
246 for (parm = DECL_ARGUMENTS (fndecl); parm; parm = DECL_CHAIN (parm))
247 count++;
248
249 return count;
250}

252/* Return the declaration of Ith formal parameter of the function corresponding
253 to INFO. Note there is no setter function as this array is built just once
254 using ipa_initialize_node_params. */
255
256void
257ipa_dump_param (FILE *file, struct ipa_node_params *info, int i)
258{
259 fprintf (file, "param #%i", i);
260 if ((*info->descriptors)[i].decl_or_type)
261 {
262 fprintf (file, " ");
263 print_generic_expr (file, (*info->descriptors)[i].decl_or_type, 0);
264 }
265}

267/* If necessary, allocate vector of parameter descriptors in info of NODE.
268 Return true if they were allocated, false if not. */
269
270static bool
271ipa_alloc_node_params (struct cgraph_node *node, int param_count)
272{
273 struct ipa_node_params *info = IPA_NODE_REF (node);
274
275 if (!info->descriptors && param_count)
276 {
277 vec_safe_grow_cleared (info->descriptors, param_count);
278 return true;
279 }
280 else
281 return false;
282}
283
284/* Initialize the ipa_node_params structure associated with NODE by counting
285 the function parameters, creating the descriptors and populating their
286 param_decls. */
287
288void
289ipa_initialize_node_params (struct cgraph_node *node)
290{
291 struct ipa_node_params *info = IPA_NODE_REF (node);
292
293 if (!info->descriptors
294 && ipa_alloc_node_params (node, count_formal_params (node->decl)))
295 ipa_populate_param_decls (node, *info->descriptors);
296}

298/* Print the jump functions associated with call graph edge CS to file F. */
299
300static void
301ipa_print_node_jump_functions_for_edge (FILE *f, struct cgraph_edge *cs)
302{
303 int i, count;
304
305 count = ipa_get_cs_argument_count (IPA_EDGE_REF (cs));
306 for (i = 0; i < count; i++)
307 {
308 struct ipa_jump_func *jump_func;
309 enum jump_func_type type;
310
311 jump_func = ipa_get_ith_jump_func (IPA_EDGE_REF (cs), i);
312 type = jump_func->type;
313
314 fprintf (f, " param %d: ", i);
315 if (type == IPA_JF_UNKNOWN)
316 fprintf (f, "UNKNOWN\n");
317 else if (type == IPA_JF_CONST)
318 {
319 tree val = jump_func->value.constant.value;
320 fprintf (f, "CONST: ");
321 print_generic_expr (f, val, 0);
322 if (TREE_CODE (val) == ADDR_EXPR
323 && TREE_CODE (TREE_OPERAND (val, 0)) == CONST_DECL)
324 {
325 fprintf (f, " -> ");
326 print_generic_expr (f, DECL_INITIAL (TREE_OPERAND (val, 0)),
327 0);
328 }
329 fprintf (f, "\n");
330 }
331 else if (type == IPA_JF_PASS_THROUGH)
332 {
333 fprintf (f, "PASS THROUGH: ");
334 fprintf (f, "%d, op %s",
335 jump_func->value.pass_through.formal_id,
336 get_tree_code_name(jump_func->value.pass_through.operation));
337 if (jump_func->value.pass_through.operation != NOP_EXPR)
338 {
339 fprintf (f, " ");
340 print_generic_expr (f,
341 jump_func->value.pass_through.operand, 0);
342 }
343 if (jump_func->value.pass_through.agg_preserved)
344 fprintf (f, ", agg_preserved");
345 fprintf (f, "\n");
346 }
347 else if (type == IPA_JF_ANCESTOR)
348 {
349 fprintf (f, "ANCESTOR: ");
350 fprintf (f, "%d, offset " HOST_WIDE_INT_PRINT_DEC,
351 jump_func->value.ancestor.formal_id,
352 jump_func->value.ancestor.offset);
353 if (jump_func->value.ancestor.agg_preserved)
354 fprintf (f, ", agg_preserved");
355 fprintf (f, "\n");
356 }
357
358 if (jump_func->agg.items)
359 {
360 struct ipa_agg_jf_item *item;
361 int j;
362
363 fprintf (f, " Aggregate passed by %s:\n",
364 jump_func->agg.by_ref ? "reference" : "value");
365 FOR_EACH_VEC_SAFE_ELT (jump_func->agg.items, j, item)
366 {
367 fprintf (f, " offset: " HOST_WIDE_INT_PRINT_DEC ", ",
368 item->offset);
369 if (TYPE_P (item->value))
370 fprintf (f, "clobber of " HOST_WIDE_INT_PRINT_DEC " bits",
371 tree_to_uhwi (TYPE_SIZE (item->value)));
372 else
373 {
374 fprintf (f, "cst: ");
375 print_generic_expr (f, item->value, 0);
376 }
377 fprintf (f, "\n");
378 }
379 }
380
381 struct ipa_polymorphic_call_context *ctx
382 = ipa_get_ith_polymorhic_call_context (IPA_EDGE_REF (cs), i);
383 if (ctx && !ctx->useless_p ())
384 {
385 fprintf (f, " Context: ");
386 ctx->dump (dump_file);
387 }
388
389 if (jump_func->bits)
390 {
391 fprintf (f, " value: ");
392 print_hex (jump_func->bits->value, f);
393 fprintf (f, ", mask: ");
394 print_hex (jump_func->bits->mask, f);
395 fprintf (f, "\n");
396 }
397 else
398 fprintf (f, " Unknown bits\n");
399
400 if (jump_func->m_vr)
401 {
402 fprintf (f, " VR ");
403 fprintf (f, "%s[",
404 (jump_func->m_vr->type == VR_ANTI_RANGE) ? "~" : "");
405 print_decs (jump_func->m_vr->min, f);
406 fprintf (f, ", ");
407 print_decs (jump_func->m_vr->max, f);
408 fprintf (f, "]\n");
409 }
410 else
411 fprintf (f, " Unknown VR\n");
412 }
413}

416/* Print the jump functions of all arguments on all call graph edges going from
417 NODE to file F. */
418
419void
420ipa_print_node_jump_functions (FILE *f, struct cgraph_node *node)
421{
422 struct cgraph_edge *cs;
423
424 fprintf (f, " Jump functions of caller %s/%i:\n", node->name (),
425 node->order);
426 for (cs = node->callees; cs; cs = cs->next_callee)
427 {
428 if (!ipa_edge_args_info_available_for_edge_p (cs))
429 continue;
430
431 fprintf (f, " callsite %s/%i -> %s/%i : \n",
432 xstrdup_for_dump (node->name ()), node->order,
433 xstrdup_for_dump (cs->callee->name ()),
434 cs->callee->order);
435 ipa_print_node_jump_functions_for_edge (f, cs);
436 }
437
438 for (cs = node->indirect_calls; cs; cs = cs->next_callee)
439 {
440 struct cgraph_indirect_call_info *ii;
441 if (!ipa_edge_args_info_available_for_edge_p (cs))
442 continue;
443
444 ii = cs->indirect_info;
445 if (ii->agg_contents)
446 fprintf (f, " indirect %s callsite, calling param %i, "
447 "offset " HOST_WIDE_INT_PRINT_DEC ", %s",
448 ii->member_ptr ? "member ptr" : "aggregate",
449 ii->param_index, ii->offset,
450 ii->by_ref ? "by reference" : "by_value");
451 else
452 fprintf (f, " indirect %s callsite, calling param %i, "
453 "offset " HOST_WIDE_INT_PRINT_DEC,
454 ii->polymorphic ? "polymorphic" : "simple", ii->param_index,
455 ii->offset);
456
457 if (cs->call_stmt)
458 {
459 fprintf (f, ", for stmt ");
460 print_gimple_stmt (f, cs->call_stmt, 0, TDF_SLIM);
461 }
462 else
463 fprintf (f, "\n");
464 if (ii->polymorphic)
465 ii->context.dump (f);
466 ipa_print_node_jump_functions_for_edge (f, cs);
467 }
468}

470/* Print ipa_jump_func data structures of all nodes in the call graph to F. */
471
472void
473ipa_print_all_jump_functions (FILE *f)
474{
475 struct cgraph_node *node;
476
477 fprintf (f, "\nJump functions:\n");
478 FOR_EACH_FUNCTION (node)
479 {
480 ipa_print_node_jump_functions (f, node);
481 }
482}

495 combination code). The two functions will share their rdesc. */
496
497static void
498ipa_set_jf_cst_copy (struct ipa_jump_func *dst,
499 struct ipa_jump_func *src)
500

503 dst->type = IPA_JF_CONST;
504 dst->value.constant = src->value.constant;
505}
506
507/* Set JFUNC to be a constant jmp function. */
508
509static void
510ipa_set_jf_constant (struct ipa_jump_func *jfunc, tree constant,
511 struct cgraph_edge *cs)
512{
513 jfunc->type = IPA_JF_CONST;
514 jfunc->value.constant.value = unshare_expr_without_location (constant);
515
516 if (TREE_CODE (constant) == ADDR_EXPR
517 && TREE_CODE (TREE_OPERAND (constant, 0)) == FUNCTION_DECL)
518 {
519 struct ipa_cst_ref_desc *rdesc;
520
521 rdesc = ipa_refdesc_pool.allocate ();
522 rdesc->cs = cs;
523 rdesc->next_duplicate = NULL;
524 rdesc->refcount = 1;
525 jfunc->value.constant.rdesc = rdesc;
526 }
527 else
528 jfunc->value.constant.rdesc = NULL;
529}

590/* Structure to be passed in between detect_type_change and
591 check_stmt_for_type_change. */
592
593struct prop_type_change_info
594{
595 /* Offset into the object where there is the virtual method pointer we are
596 looking for. */
597 HOST_WIDE_INT offset;
598 /* The declaration or SSA_NAME pointer of the base that we are checking for
599 type change. */
600 tree object;
601 /* Set to true if dynamic type change has been detected. */
602 bool type_maybe_changed;
603};
604
605/* Return true if STMT can modify a virtual method table pointer.
606
607 This function makes special assumptions about both constructors and
608 destructors which are all the functions that are allowed to alter the VMT
609 pointers. It assumes that destructors begin with assignment into all VMT
610 pointers and that constructors essentially look in the following way:
611
612 1) The very first thing they do is that they call constructors of ancestor
613 sub-objects that have them.
614
615 2) Then VMT pointers of this and all its ancestors is set to new values
616 corresponding to the type corresponding to the constructor.
617
618 3) Only afterwards, other stuff such as constructor of member sub-objects
619 and the code written by the user is run. Only this may include calling
620 virtual functions, directly or indirectly.
621
622 There is no way to call a constructor of an ancestor sub-object in any
623 other way.
624
625 This means that we do not have to care whether constructors get the correct
626 type information because they will always change it (in fact, if we define
627 the type to be given by the VMT pointer, it is undefined).
628
629 The most important fact to derive from the above is that if, for some
630 statement in the section 3, we try to detect whether the dynamic type has
631 changed, we can safely ignore all calls as we examine the function body
632 backwards until we reach statements in section 2 because these calls cannot
633 be ancestor constructors or destructors (if the input is not bogus) and so
634 do not change the dynamic type (this holds true only for automatically
635 allocated objects but at the moment we devirtualize only these). We then
636 must detect that statements in section 2 change the dynamic type and can try
637 to derive the new type. That is enough and we can stop, we will never see
638 the calls into constructors of sub-objects in this code. Therefore we can
639 safely ignore all call statements that we traverse.
640 */
641
642static bool
643stmt_may_be_vtbl_ptr_store (gimple *stmt)
644{
645 if (is_gimple_call (stmt))
646 return false;
647 if (gimple_clobber_p (stmt))
648 return false;
649 else if (is_gimple_assign (stmt))
650 {
651 tree lhs = gimple_assign_lhs (stmt);
652
653 if (!AGGREGATE_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (lhs)))
654 {
655 if (flag_strict_aliasing
656 && !POINTER_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (lhs)))
657 return false;
658
659 if (TREE_CODE (lhs) == COMPONENT_REF
660 && !DECL_VIRTUAL_P (TREE_OPERAND (lhs, 1)))
661 return false;
662 /* In the future we might want to use get_base_ref_and_offset to find
663 if there is a field corresponding to the offset and if so, proceed
664 almost like if it was a component ref. */
665 }
666 }
667 return true;
668}
669
670/* Callback of walk_aliased_vdefs and a helper function for detect_type_change
671 to check whether a particular statement may modify the virtual table
672 pointerIt stores its result into DATA, which points to a
673 prop_type_change_info structure. */
674
675static bool
676check_stmt_for_type_change (ao_ref *ao ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED, tree vdef, void *data)
677{
678 gimple *stmt = SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (vdef);
679 struct prop_type_change_info *tci = (struct prop_type_change_info *) data;
680
681 if (stmt_may_be_vtbl_ptr_store (stmt))
682 {
683 tci->type_maybe_changed = true;
684 return true;
685 }
686 else
687 return false;
688}
689
690/* See if ARG is PARAM_DECl describing instance passed by pointer
691 or reference in FUNCTION. Return false if the dynamic type may change
692 in between beggining of the function until CALL is invoked.
693
694 Generally functions are not allowed to change type of such instances,
695 but they call destructors. We assume that methods can not destroy the THIS
696 pointer. Also as a special cases, constructor and destructors may change
697 type of the THIS pointer. */
698
699static bool
700param_type_may_change_p (tree function, tree arg, gimple *call)
701{
702 /* Pure functions can not do any changes on the dynamic type;
703 that require writting to memory. */
704 if (flags_from_decl_or_type (function) & (ECF_PURE | ECF_CONST))
705 return false;
706 /* We need to check if we are within inlined consturctor
707 or destructor (ideally we would have way to check that the
708 inline cdtor is actually working on ARG, but we don't have
709 easy tie on this, so punt on all non-pure cdtors.
710 We may also record the types of cdtors and once we know type
711 of the instance match them.
712
713 Also code unification optimizations may merge calls from
714 different blocks making return values unreliable. So
715 do nothing during late optimization. */
716 if (DECL_STRUCT_FUNCTION (function)->after_inlining)
717 return true;
718 if (TREE_CODE (arg) == SSA_NAME
719 && SSA_NAME_IS_DEFAULT_DEF (arg)
720 && TREE_CODE (SSA_NAME_VAR (arg)) == PARM_DECL)
721 {
722 /* Normal (non-THIS) argument. */
723 if ((SSA_NAME_VAR (arg) != DECL_ARGUMENTS (function)
724 || TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (function)) != METHOD_TYPE)
725 /* THIS pointer of an method - here we want to watch constructors
726 and destructors as those definitely may change the dynamic
727 type. */
728 || (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (function)) == METHOD_TYPE
729 && !DECL_CXX_CONSTRUCTOR_P (function)
730 && !DECL_CXX_DESTRUCTOR_P (function)
731 && (SSA_NAME_VAR (arg) == DECL_ARGUMENTS (function))))
732 {
733 /* Walk the inline stack and watch out for ctors/dtors. */
734 for (tree block = gimple_block (call); block && TREE_CODE (block) == BLOCK;
735 block = BLOCK_SUPERCONTEXT (block))
736 if (inlined_polymorphic_ctor_dtor_block_p (block, false))
737 return true;
738 return false;
739 }
740 }
741 return true;
742}
743
744/* Detect whether the dynamic type of ARG of COMP_TYPE has changed (before
745 callsite CALL) by looking for assignments to its virtual table pointer. If
746 it is, return true and fill in the jump function JFUNC with relevant type
747 information or set it to unknown. ARG is the object itself (not a pointer
748 to it, unless dereferenced). BASE is the base of the memory access as
749 returned by get_ref_base_and_extent, as is the offset.
750
751 This is helper function for detect_type_change and detect_type_change_ssa
752 that does the heavy work which is usually unnecesary. */
753
754static bool
755detect_type_change_from_memory_writes (tree arg, tree base, tree comp_type,
756 gcall *call, struct ipa_jump_func *jfunc,
757 HOST_WIDE_INT offset)
758{
759 struct prop_type_change_info tci;
760 ao_ref ao;
761 bool entry_reached = false;
762
763 gcc_checking_assert (DECL_P (arg)
764 || TREE_CODE (arg) == MEM_REF
765 || handled_component_p (arg));
766
767 comp_type = TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (comp_type);
768
769 /* Const calls cannot call virtual methods through VMT and so type changes do
770 not matter. */
771 if (!flag_devirtualize || !gimple_vuse (call)
772 /* Be sure expected_type is polymorphic. */
773 || !comp_type
774 || TREE_CODE (comp_type) != RECORD_TYPE
775 || !TYPE_BINFO (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (comp_type))
776 || !BINFO_VTABLE (TYPE_BINFO (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (comp_type))))
777 return true;
778
779 ao_ref_init (&ao, arg);
780 ao.base = base;
781 ao.offset = offset;
782 ao.size = POINTER_SIZE;
783 ao.max_size = ao.size;
784
785 tci.offset = offset;
786 tci.object = get_base_address (arg);
787 tci.type_maybe_changed = false;
788
789 walk_aliased_vdefs (&ao, gimple_vuse (call), check_stmt_for_type_change,
790 &tci, NULL, &entry_reached);
791 if (!tci.type_maybe_changed)
792 return false;
793
794 ipa_set_jf_unknown (jfunc);
795 return true;
796}
797
798/* Detect whether the dynamic type of ARG of COMP_TYPE may have changed.
799 If it is, return true and fill in the jump function JFUNC with relevant type
800 information or set it to unknown. ARG is the object itself (not a pointer
801 to it, unless dereferenced). BASE is the base of the memory access as
802 returned by get_ref_base_and_extent, as is the offset. */
803
804static bool
805detect_type_change (tree arg, tree base, tree comp_type, gcall *call,
806 struct ipa_jump_func *jfunc, HOST_WIDE_INT offset)
807{
808 if (!flag_devirtualize)
809 return false;
810
811 if (TREE_CODE (base) == MEM_REF
812 && !param_type_may_change_p (current_function_decl,
813 TREE_OPERAND (base, 0),
814 call))
815 return false;
816 return detect_type_change_from_memory_writes (arg, base, comp_type,
817 call, jfunc, offset);
818}
819
820/* Like detect_type_change but ARG is supposed to be a non-dereferenced pointer
821 SSA name (its dereference will become the base and the offset is assumed to
822 be zero). */
823
824static bool
825detect_type_change_ssa (tree arg, tree comp_type,
826 gcall *call, struct ipa_jump_func *jfunc)
827{
828 gcc_checking_assert (TREE_CODE (arg) == SSA_NAME);
829 if (!flag_devirtualize
830 || !POINTER_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (arg)))
831 return false;
832
833 if (!param_type_may_change_p (current_function_decl, arg, call))
834 return false;
835
836 arg = build2 (MEM_REF, ptr_type_node, arg,
837 build_int_cst (ptr_type_node, 0));
838
839 return detect_type_change_from_memory_writes (arg, arg, comp_type,
840 call, jfunc, 0);
841}
842
843/* Callback of walk_aliased_vdefs. Flags that it has been invoked to the
844 boolean variable pointed to by DATA. */
845
846static bool
847mark_modified (ao_ref *ao ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED, tree vdef ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED,
848 void *data)
849{
850 bool *b = (bool *) data;
851 *b = true;
852 return true;
853}
854
855/* Return true if we have already walked so many statements in AA that we
856 should really just start giving up. */
857
858static bool
859aa_overwalked (struct ipa_func_body_info *fbi)
860{
861 gcc_checking_assert (fbi);
862 return fbi->aa_walked > (unsigned) PARAM_VALUE (PARAM_IPA_MAX_AA_STEPS);
863}
864
865/* Find the nearest valid aa status for parameter specified by INDEX that
866 dominates BB. */
867
868static struct ipa_param_aa_status *
869find_dominating_aa_status (struct ipa_func_body_info *fbi, basic_block bb,
870 int index)
871{
872 while (true)
873 {
874 bb = get_immediate_dominator (CDI_DOMINATORS, bb);
875 if (!bb)
876 return NULL;
877 struct ipa_bb_info *bi = ipa_get_bb_info (fbi, bb);
878 if (!bi->param_aa_statuses.is_empty ()
879 && bi->param_aa_statuses[index].valid)
880 return &bi->param_aa_statuses[index];
881 }
882}
883
884/* Get AA status structure for the given BB and parameter with INDEX. Allocate
885 structures and/or intialize the result with a dominating description as
886 necessary. */
887
888static struct ipa_param_aa_status *
889parm_bb_aa_status_for_bb (struct ipa_func_body_info *fbi, basic_block bb,
890 int index)
891{
892 gcc_checking_assert (fbi);
893 struct ipa_bb_info *bi = ipa_get_bb_info (fbi, bb);
894 if (bi->param_aa_statuses.is_empty ())
895 bi->param_aa_statuses.safe_grow_cleared (fbi->param_count);
896 struct ipa_param_aa_status *paa = &bi->param_aa_statuses[index];
897 if (!paa->valid)
898 {
899 gcc_checking_assert (!paa->parm_modified
900 && !paa->ref_modified
901 && !paa->pt_modified);
902 struct ipa_param_aa_status *dom_paa;
903 dom_paa = find_dominating_aa_status (fbi, bb, index);
904 if (dom_paa)
905 *paa = *dom_paa;
906 else
907 paa->valid = true;
908 }
909
910 return paa;
911}
912
913/* Return true if a load from a formal parameter PARM_LOAD is known to retrieve
914 a value known not to be modified in this function before reaching the
915 statement STMT. FBI holds information about the function we have so far
916 gathered but do not survive the summary building stage. */
917
918static bool
919parm_preserved_before_stmt_p (struct ipa_func_body_info *fbi, int index,
920 gimple *stmt, tree parm_load)
921{
922 struct ipa_param_aa_status *paa;
923 bool modified = false;
924 ao_ref refd;
925
926 tree base = get_base_address (parm_load);
927 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (base) == PARM_DECL);
928 if (TREE_READONLY (base))
929 return true;
930
931 /* FIXME: FBI can be NULL if we are being called from outside
932 ipa_node_analysis or ipcp_transform_function, which currently happens
933 during inlining analysis. It would be great to extend fbi's lifetime and
934 always have it. Currently, we are just not afraid of too much walking in
935 that case. */
936 if (fbi)
937 {
938 if (aa_overwalked (fbi))
939 return false;
940 paa = parm_bb_aa_status_for_bb (fbi, gimple_bb (stmt), index);
941 if (paa->parm_modified)
942 return false;
943 }
944 else
945 paa = NULL;
946
947 gcc_checking_assert (gimple_vuse (stmt) != NULL_TREE);
948 ao_ref_init (&refd, parm_load);
949 int walked = walk_aliased_vdefs (&refd, gimple_vuse (stmt), mark_modified,
950 &modified, NULL);
951 if (fbi)
952 fbi->aa_walked += walked;
953 if (paa && modified)
954 paa->parm_modified = true;
955 return !modified;
956}
957
958/* If STMT is an assignment that loads a value from an parameter declaration,
959 return the index of the parameter in ipa_node_params which has not been
960 modified. Otherwise return -1. */
961
962static int
963load_from_unmodified_param (struct ipa_func_body_info *fbi,
964 vec<ipa_param_descriptor, va_gc> *descriptors,
965 gimple *stmt)
966{
967 int index;
968 tree op1;
969
970 if (!gimple_assign_single_p (stmt))
971 return -1;
972
973 op1 = gimple_assign_rhs1 (stmt);
974 if (TREE_CODE (op1) != PARM_DECL)
975 return -1;
976
977 index = ipa_get_param_decl_index_1 (descriptors, op1);
978 if (index < 0
979 || !parm_preserved_before_stmt_p (fbi, index, stmt, op1))
980 return -1;
981
982 return index;
983}
984
985/* Return true if memory reference REF (which must be a load through parameter
986 with INDEX) loads data that are known to be unmodified in this function
987 before reaching statement STMT. */
988
989static bool
990parm_ref_data_preserved_p (struct ipa_func_body_info *fbi,
991 int index, gimple *stmt, tree ref)
992{
993 struct ipa_param_aa_status *paa;
994 bool modified = false;
995 ao_ref refd;
996
997 /* FIXME: FBI can be NULL if we are being called from outside
998 ipa_node_analysis or ipcp_transform_function, which currently happens
999 during inlining analysis. It would be great to extend fbi's lifetime and
1000 always have it. Currently, we are just not afraid of too much walking in
1001 that case. */
1002 if (fbi)
1003 {
1004 if (aa_overwalked (fbi))
1005 return false;
1006 paa = parm_bb_aa_status_for_bb (fbi, gimple_bb (stmt), index);
1007 if (paa->ref_modified)
1008 return false;
1009 }
1010 else
1011 paa = NULL;
1012
1013 gcc_checking_assert (gimple_vuse (stmt));
1014 ao_ref_init (&refd, ref);
1015 int walked = walk_aliased_vdefs (&refd, gimple_vuse (stmt), mark_modified,
1016 &modified, NULL);
1017 if (fbi)
1018 fbi->aa_walked += walked;
1019 if (paa && modified)
1020 paa->ref_modified = true;
1021 return !modified;
1022}
1023
1024/* Return true if the data pointed to by PARM (which is a parameter with INDEX)
1025 is known to be unmodified in this function before reaching call statement
1026 CALL into which it is passed. FBI describes the function body. */
1027
1028static bool
1029parm_ref_data_pass_through_p (struct ipa_func_body_info *fbi, int index,
1030 gimple *call, tree parm)
1031{
1032 bool modified = false;
1033 ao_ref refd;
1034
1035 /* It's unnecessary to calculate anything about memory contnets for a const
1036 function because it is not goin to use it. But do not cache the result
1037 either. Also, no such calculations for non-pointers. */
1038 if (!gimple_vuse (call)
1039 || !POINTER_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (parm))
1040 || aa_overwalked (fbi))
1041 return false;
1042
1043 struct ipa_param_aa_status *paa = parm_bb_aa_status_for_bb (fbi,
1044 gimple_bb (call),
1045 index);
1046 if (paa->pt_modified)
1047 return false;
1048
1049 ao_ref_init_from_ptr_and_size (&refd, parm, NULL_TREE);
1050 int walked = walk_aliased_vdefs (&refd, gimple_vuse (call), mark_modified,
1051 &modified, NULL);
1052 fbi->aa_walked += walked;
1053 if (modified)
1054 paa->pt_modified = true;
1055 return !modified;
1056}
1057
1058/* Return true if we can prove that OP is a memory reference loading
1059 data from an aggregate passed as a parameter.
1060
1061 The function works in two modes. If GUARANTEED_UNMODIFIED is NULL, it return
1062 false if it cannot prove that the value has not been modified before the
1063 load in STMT. If GUARANTEED_UNMODIFIED is not NULL, it will return true even
1064 if it cannot prove the value has not been modified, in that case it will
1065 store false to *GUARANTEED_UNMODIFIED, otherwise it will store true there.
1066
1067 INFO and PARMS_AINFO describe parameters of the current function (but the
1068 latter can be NULL), STMT is the load statement. If function returns true,
1069 *INDEX_P, *OFFSET_P and *BY_REF is filled with the parameter index, offset
1070 within the aggregate and whether it is a load from a value passed by
1071 reference respectively. */
1072
1073bool
1074ipa_load_from_parm_agg (struct ipa_func_body_info *fbi,
1075 vec<ipa_param_descriptor, va_gc> *descriptors,
1076 gimple *stmt, tree op, int *index_p,
1077 HOST_WIDE_INT *offset_p, HOST_WIDE_INT *size_p,
1078 bool *by_ref_p, bool *guaranteed_unmodified)
1079{
1080 int index;
1081 HOST_WIDE_INT size, max_size;
1082 bool reverse;
1083 tree base
1084 = get_ref_base_and_extent (op, offset_p, &size, &max_size, &reverse);
1085
1086 if (max_size == -1 || max_size != size || *offset_p < 0)
1087 return false;
1088
1089 if (DECL_P (base))
1090 {
1091 int index = ipa_get_param_decl_index_1 (descriptors, base);
1092 if (index >= 0
1093 && parm_preserved_before_stmt_p (fbi, index, stmt, op))
1094 {
1095 *index_p = index;
1096 *by_ref_p = false;
1097 if (size_p)
1098 *size_p = size;
1099 if (guaranteed_unmodified)
1100 *guaranteed_unmodified = true;
1101 return true;
1102 }
1103 return false;
1104 }
1105
1106 if (TREE_CODE (base) != MEM_REF
1107 || TREE_CODE (TREE_OPERAND (base, 0)) != SSA_NAME
1108 || !integer_zerop (TREE_OPERAND (base, 1)))
1109 return false;
1110
1111 if (SSA_NAME_IS_DEFAULT_DEF (TREE_OPERAND (base, 0)))
1112 {
1113 tree parm = SSA_NAME_VAR (TREE_OPERAND (base, 0));
1114 index = ipa_get_param_decl_index_1 (descriptors, parm);
1115 }
1116 else
1117 {
1118 /* This branch catches situations where a pointer parameter is not a
1119 gimple register, for example:
1120
1121 void hip7(S*) (struct S * p)
1122 {
1123 void (*<T2e4>) (struct S *) D.1867;
1124 struct S * p.1;
1125
1126 <bb 2>:
1127 p.1_1 = p;
1128 D.1867_2 = p.1_1->f;
1129 D.1867_2 ();
1130 gdp = &p;
1131 */
1132
1133 gimple *def = SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (TREE_OPERAND (base, 0));
1134 index = load_from_unmodified_param (fbi, descriptors, def);
1135 }
1136
1137 if (index >= 0)
1138 {
1139 bool data_preserved = parm_ref_data_preserved_p (fbi, index, stmt, op);
1140 if (!data_preserved && !guaranteed_unmodified)
1141 return false;
1142
1143 *index_p = index;
1144 *by_ref_p = true;
1145 if (size_p)
1146 *size_p = size;
1147 if (guaranteed_unmodified)
1148 *guaranteed_unmodified = data_preserved;
1149 return true;
1150 }
1151 return false;
1152}
1153
1154/* Given that an actual argument is an SSA_NAME (given in NAME) and is a result
1155 of an assignment statement STMT, try to determine whether we are actually
1156 handling any of the following cases and construct an appropriate jump
1157 function into JFUNC if so:
1158
1159 1) The passed value is loaded from a formal parameter which is not a gimple
1160 register (most probably because it is addressable, the value has to be
1161 scalar) and we can guarantee the value has not changed. This case can
1162 therefore be described by a simple pass-through jump function. For example:
1163
1164 foo (int a)
1165 {
1166 int a.0;
1167
1168 a.0_2 = a;
1169 bar (a.0_2);
1170
1171 2) The passed value can be described by a simple arithmetic pass-through
1172 jump function. E.g.
1173
1174 foo (int a)
1175 {
1176 int D.2064;
1177
1178 D.2064_4 = a.1(D) + 4;
1179 bar (D.2064_4);
1180
1181 This case can also occur in combination of the previous one, e.g.:
1182
1183 foo (int a, int z)
1184 {
1185 int a.0;
1186 int D.2064;
1187
1188 a.0_3 = a;
1189 D.2064_4 = a.0_3 + 4;
1190 foo (D.2064_4);
1191
1192 3) The passed value is an address of an object within another one (which
1193 also passed by reference). Such situations are described by an ancestor
1194 jump function and describe situations such as:
1195
1196 B::foo() (struct B * const this)
1197 {
1198 struct A * D.1845;
1199
1200 D.1845_2 = &this_1(D)->D.1748;
1201 A::bar (D.1845_2);
1202
1203 INFO is the structure describing individual parameters access different
1204 stages of IPA optimizations. PARMS_AINFO contains the information that is
1205 only needed for intraprocedural analysis. */
1206
1207static void
1208compute_complex_assign_jump_func (struct ipa_func_body_info *fbi,
1209 struct ipa_node_params *info,
1210 struct ipa_jump_func *jfunc,
1211 gcall *call, gimple *stmt, tree name,
1212 tree param_type)
1213{
1214 HOST_WIDE_INT offset, size, max_size;
1215 tree op1, tc_ssa, base, ssa;
1216 bool reverse;
1217 int index;
1218
1219 op1 = gimple_assign_rhs1 (stmt);
1220
1221 if (TREE_CODE (op1) == SSA_NAME)
1222 {
1223 if (SSA_NAME_IS_DEFAULT_DEF (op1))
1224 index = ipa_get_param_decl_index (info, SSA_NAME_VAR (op1));
1225 else
1226 index = load_from_unmodified_param (fbi, info->descriptors,
1227 SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (op1));
1228 tc_ssa = op1;
1229 }
1230 else
1231 {
1232 index = load_from_unmodified_param (fbi, info->descriptors, stmt);
1233 tc_ssa = gimple_assign_lhs (stmt);
1234 }
1235
1236 if (index >= 0)
1237 {
1238 switch (gimple_assign_rhs_class (stmt))
1239 {
1240 case GIMPLE_BINARY_RHS:
1241 {
1242 tree op2 = gimple_assign_rhs2 (stmt);
1243 if (!is_gimple_ip_invariant (op2)
1244 || ((TREE_CODE_CLASS (gimple_assign_rhs_code (stmt))
1245 != tcc_comparison)
1246 && !useless_type_conversion_p (TREE_TYPE (name),
1247 TREE_TYPE (op1))))
1248 return;
1249
1250 ipa_set_jf_arith_pass_through (jfunc, index, op2,
1251 gimple_assign_rhs_code (stmt));
1252 break;
1253 }
1254 case GIMPLE_SINGLE_RHS:
1255 {
1256 bool agg_p = parm_ref_data_pass_through_p (fbi, index, call,
1257 tc_ssa);
1258 ipa_set_jf_simple_pass_through (jfunc, index, agg_p);
1259 break;
1260 }
1261 case GIMPLE_UNARY_RHS:
1262 if (is_gimple_assign (stmt)
1263 && gimple_assign_rhs_class (stmt) == GIMPLE_UNARY_RHS
1264 && ! CONVERT_EXPR_CODE_P (gimple_assign_rhs_code (stmt)))
1265 ipa_set_jf_unary_pass_through (jfunc, index,
1266 gimple_assign_rhs_code (stmt));
1267 default:;
1268 }
1269 return;
1270 }
1271
1272 if (TREE_CODE (op1) != ADDR_EXPR)
1273 return;
1274 op1 = TREE_OPERAND (op1, 0);
1275 if (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (op1)) != RECORD_TYPE)
1276 return;
1277 base = get_ref_base_and_extent (op1, &offset, &size, &max_size, &reverse);
1278 if (TREE_CODE (base) != MEM_REF
1279 /* If this is a varying address, punt. */
1280 || max_size == -1
1281 || max_size != size)
1282 return;
1283 offset += mem_ref_offset (base).to_short_addr () * BITS_PER_UNIT;
1284 ssa = TREE_OPERAND (base, 0);
1285 if (TREE_CODE (ssa) != SSA_NAME
1286 || !SSA_NAME_IS_DEFAULT_DEF (ssa)
1287 || offset < 0)
1288 return;
1289
1290 /* Dynamic types are changed in constructors and destructors. */
1291 index = ipa_get_param_decl_index (info, SSA_NAME_VAR (ssa));
1292 if (index >= 0 && param_type && POINTER_TYPE_P (param_type))
1293 ipa_set_ancestor_jf (jfunc, offset, index,
1294 parm_ref_data_pass_through_p (fbi, index, call, ssa));
1295}
1296
1297/* Extract the base, offset and MEM_REF expression from a statement ASSIGN if
1298 it looks like:
1299
1300 iftmp.1_3 = &obj_2(D)->D.1762;
1301
1302 The base of the MEM_REF must be a default definition SSA NAME of a
1303 parameter. Return NULL_TREE if it looks otherwise. If case of success, the
1304 whole MEM_REF expression is returned and the offset calculated from any
1305 handled components and the MEM_REF itself is stored into *OFFSET. The whole
1306 RHS stripped off the ADDR_EXPR is stored into *OBJ_P. */
1307
1308static tree
1309get_ancestor_addr_info (gimple *assign, tree *obj_p, HOST_WIDE_INT *offset)
1310{
1311 HOST_WIDE_INT size, max_size;
1312 tree expr, parm, obj;
1313 bool reverse;
1314
1315 if (!gimple_assign_single_p (assign))
1316 return NULL_TREE;
1317 expr = gimple_assign_rhs1 (assign);
1318
1319 if (TREE_CODE (expr) != ADDR_EXPR)
1320 return NULL_TREE;
1321 expr = TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0);
1322 obj = expr;
1323 expr = get_ref_base_and_extent (expr, offset, &size, &max_size, &reverse);
1324
1325 if (TREE_CODE (expr) != MEM_REF
1326 /* If this is a varying address, punt. */
1327 || max_size == -1
1328 || max_size != size
1329 || *offset < 0)
1330 return NULL_TREE;
1331 parm = TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0);
1332 if (TREE_CODE (parm) != SSA_NAME
1333 || !SSA_NAME_IS_DEFAULT_DEF (parm)
1334 || TREE_CODE (SSA_NAME_VAR (parm)) != PARM_DECL)
1335 return NULL_TREE;
1336
1337 *offset += mem_ref_offset (expr).to_short_addr () * BITS_PER_UNIT;
1338 *obj_p = obj;
1339 return expr;
1340}
1341
1342
1343/* Given that an actual argument is an SSA_NAME that is a result of a phi
1344 statement PHI, try to find out whether NAME is in fact a
1345 multiple-inheritance typecast from a descendant into an ancestor of a formal
1346 parameter and thus can be described by an ancestor jump function and if so,
1347 write the appropriate function into JFUNC.
1348
1349 Essentially we want to match the following pattern:
1350
1351 if (obj_2(D) != 0B)
1352 goto <bb 3>;
1353 else
1354 goto <bb 4>;
1355
1356 <bb 3>:
1357 iftmp.1_3 = &obj_2(D)->D.1762;
1358
1359 <bb 4>:
1360 # iftmp.1_1 = PHI <iftmp.1_3(3), 0B(2)>
1361 D.1879_6 = middleman_1 (iftmp.1_1, i_5(D));
1362 return D.1879_6; */
1363
1364static void
1365compute_complex_ancestor_jump_func (struct ipa_func_body_info *fbi,
1366 struct ipa_node_params *info,
1367 struct ipa_jump_func *jfunc,
1368 gcall *call, gphi *phi)
1369{
1370 HOST_WIDE_INT offset;
1371 gimple *assign, *cond;
1372 basic_block phi_bb, assign_bb, cond_bb;
1373 tree tmp, parm, expr, obj;
1374 int index, i;
1375
1376 if (gimple_phi_num_args (phi) != 2)
1377 return;
1378
1379 if (integer_zerop (PHI_ARG_DEF (phi, 1)))
1380 tmp = PHI_ARG_DEF (phi, 0);
1381 else if (integer_zerop (PHI_ARG_DEF (phi, 0)))
1382 tmp = PHI_ARG_DEF (phi, 1);
1383 else
1384 return;
1385 if (TREE_CODE (tmp) != SSA_NAME
1386 || SSA_NAME_IS_DEFAULT_DEF (tmp)
1387 || !POINTER_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (tmp))
1388 || TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (TREE_TYPE (tmp))) != RECORD_TYPE)
1389 return;
1390
1391 assign = SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (tmp);
1392 assign_bb = gimple_bb (assign);
1393 if (!single_pred_p (assign_bb))
1394 return;
1395 expr = get_ancestor_addr_info (assign, &obj, &offset);
1396 if (!expr)
1397 return;
1398 parm = TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0);
1399 index = ipa_get_param_decl_index (info, SSA_NAME_VAR (parm));
1400 if (index < 0)
1401 return;
1402
1403 cond_bb = single_pred (assign_bb);
1404 cond = last_stmt (cond_bb);
1405 if (!cond
1406 || gimple_code (cond) != GIMPLE_COND
1407 || gimple_cond_code (cond) != NE_EXPR
1408 || gimple_cond_lhs (cond) != parm
1409 || !integer_zerop (gimple_cond_rhs (cond)))
1410 return;
1411
1412 phi_bb = gimple_bb (phi);
1413 for (i = 0; i < 2; i++)
1414 {
1415 basic_block pred = EDGE_PRED (phi_bb, i)->src;
1416 if (pred != assign_bb && pred != cond_bb)
1417 return;
1418 }
1419
1420 ipa_set_ancestor_jf (jfunc, offset, index,
1421 parm_ref_data_pass_through_p (fbi, index, call, parm));
1422}
1423
1424/* Inspect the given TYPE and return true iff it has the same structure (the
1425 same number of fields of the same types) as a C++ member pointer. If
1426 METHOD_PTR and DELTA are non-NULL, store the trees representing the
1427 corresponding fields there. */
1428
1429static bool
1430type_like_member_ptr_p (tree type, tree *method_ptr, tree *delta)
1431{
1432 tree fld;
1433
1434 if (TREE_CODE (type) != RECORD_TYPE)
1435 return false;
1436
1437 fld = TYPE_FIELDS (type);
1438 if (!fld || !POINTER_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (fld))
1439 || TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (TREE_TYPE (fld))) != METHOD_TYPE
1440 || !tree_fits_uhwi_p (DECL_FIELD_OFFSET (fld)))
1441 return false;
1442
1443 if (method_ptr)
1444 *method_ptr = fld;
1445
1446 fld = DECL_CHAIN (fld);
1447 if (!fld || INTEGRAL_TYPE_P (fld)
1448 || !tree_fits_uhwi_p (DECL_FIELD_OFFSET (fld)))
1449 return false;
1450 if (delta)
1451 *delta = fld;
1452
1453 if (DECL_CHAIN (fld))
1454 return false;
1455
1456 return true;
1457}
1458
1459/* If RHS is an SSA_NAME and it is defined by a simple copy assign statement,
1460 return the rhs of its defining statement. Otherwise return RHS as it
1461 is. */
1462
1463static inline tree
1464get_ssa_def_if_simple_copy (tree rhs)
1465{
1466 while (TREE_CODE (rhs) == SSA_NAME && !SSA_NAME_IS_DEFAULT_DEF (rhs))
1467 {
1468 gimple *def_stmt = SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (rhs);
1469
1470 if (gimple_assign_single_p (def_stmt))
1471 rhs = gimple_assign_rhs1 (def_stmt);
1472 else
1473 break;
1474 }
1475 return rhs;
1476}
1477
1478/* Simple linked list, describing known contents of an aggregate beforere
1479 call. */
1480
1481struct ipa_known_agg_contents_list
1482{
1483 /* Offset and size of the described part of the aggregate. */
1484 HOST_WIDE_INT offset, size;
1485 /* Known constant value or NULL if the contents is known to be unknown. */
1486 tree constant;
1487 /* Pointer to the next structure in the list. */
1488 struct ipa_known_agg_contents_list *next;
1489};
1490
1491/* Find the proper place in linked list of ipa_known_agg_contents_list
1492 structures where to put a new one with the given LHS_OFFSET and LHS_SIZE,
1493 unless there is a partial overlap, in which case return NULL, or such
1494 element is already there, in which case set *ALREADY_THERE to true. */
1495
1496static struct ipa_known_agg_contents_list **
1497get_place_in_agg_contents_list (struct ipa_known_agg_contents_list **list,
1498 HOST_WIDE_INT lhs_offset,
1499 HOST_WIDE_INT lhs_size,
1500 bool *already_there)
1501{
1502 struct ipa_known_agg_contents_list **p = list;
1503 while (*p && (*p)->offset < lhs_offset)
1504 {
1505 if ((*p)->offset + (*p)->size > lhs_offset)
1506 return NULL;
1507 p = &(*p)->next;
1508 }
1509
1510 if (*p && (*p)->offset < lhs_offset + lhs_size)
1511 {
1512 if ((*p)->offset == lhs_offset && (*p)->size == lhs_size)
1513 /* We already know this value is subsequently overwritten with
1514 something else. */
1515 *already_there = true;
1516 else
1517 /* Otherwise this is a partial overlap which we cannot
1518 represent. */
1519 return NULL;
1520 }
1521 return p;
1522}
1523
1524/* Build aggregate jump function from LIST, assuming there are exactly
1525 CONST_COUNT constant entries there and that th offset of the passed argument
1526 is ARG_OFFSET and store it into JFUNC. */
1527
1528static void
1529build_agg_jump_func_from_list (struct ipa_known_agg_contents_list *list,
1530 int const_count, HOST_WIDE_INT arg_offset,
1531 struct ipa_jump_func *jfunc)
1532{
1533 vec_alloc (jfunc->agg.items, const_count);
1534 while (list)
1535 {
1536 if (list->constant)
1537 {
1538 struct ipa_agg_jf_item item;
1539 item.offset = list->offset - arg_offset;
1540 gcc_assert ((item.offset % BITS_PER_UNIT) == 0);
1541 item.value = unshare_expr_without_location (list->constant);
1542 jfunc->agg.items->quick_push (item);
1543 }
1544 list = list->next;
1545 }
1546}
1547
1548/* Traverse statements from CALL backwards, scanning whether an aggregate given
1549 in ARG is filled in with constant values. ARG can either be an aggregate
1550 expression or a pointer to an aggregate. ARG_TYPE is the type of the
1551 aggregate. JFUNC is the jump function into which the constants are
1552 subsequently stored. */
1553
1554static void
1555determine_locally_known_aggregate_parts (gcall *call, tree arg,
1556 tree arg_type,
1557 struct ipa_jump_func *jfunc)
1558{
1559 struct ipa_known_agg_contents_list *list = NULL;
1560 int item_count = 0, const_count = 0;
1561 HOST_WIDE_INT arg_offset, arg_size;
1562 gimple_stmt_iterator gsi;
1563 tree arg_base;
1564 bool check_ref, by_ref;
1565 ao_ref r;
1566
1567 if (PARAM_VALUE (PARAM_IPA_MAX_AGG_ITEMS) == 0)
1568 return;
1569
1570 /* The function operates in three stages. First, we prepare check_ref, r,
1571 arg_base and arg_offset based on what is actually passed as an actual
1572 argument. */
1573
1574 if (POINTER_TYPE_P (arg_type))
1575 {
1576 by_ref = true;
1577 if (TREE_CODE (arg) == SSA_NAME)
1578 {
1579 tree type_size;
1580 if (!tree_fits_uhwi_p (TYPE_SIZE (TREE_TYPE (arg_type))))
1581 return;
1582 check_ref = true;
1583 arg_base = arg;
1584 arg_offset = 0;
1585 type_size = TYPE_SIZE (TREE_TYPE (arg_type));
1586 arg_size = tree_to_uhwi (type_size);
1587 ao_ref_init_from_ptr_and_size (&r, arg_base, NULL_TREE);
1588 }
1589 else if (TREE_CODE (arg) == ADDR_EXPR)
1590 {
1591 HOST_WIDE_INT arg_max_size;
1592 bool reverse;
1593
1594 arg = TREE_OPERAND (arg, 0);
1595 arg_base = get_ref_base_and_extent (arg, &arg_offset, &arg_size,
1596 &arg_max_size, &reverse);
1597 if (arg_max_size == -1
1598 || arg_max_size != arg_size
1599 || arg_offset < 0)
1600 return;
1601 if (DECL_P (arg_base))
1602 {
1603 check_ref = false;
1604 ao_ref_init (&r, arg_base);
1605 }
1606 else
1607 return;
1608 }
1609 else
1610 return;
1611 }
1612 else
1613 {
1614 HOST_WIDE_INT arg_max_size;
1615 bool reverse;
1616
1617 gcc_checking_assert (AGGREGATE_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (arg)));
1618
1619 by_ref = false;
1620 check_ref = false;
1621 arg_base = get_ref_base_and_extent (arg, &arg_offset, &arg_size,
1622 &arg_max_size, &reverse);
1623 if (arg_max_size == -1
1624 || arg_max_size != arg_size
1625 || arg_offset < 0)
1626 return;
1627
1628 ao_ref_init (&r, arg);
1629 }
1630
1631 /* Second stage walks back the BB, looks at individual statements and as long
1632 as it is confident of how the statements affect contents of the
1633 aggregates, it builds a sorted linked list of ipa_agg_jf_list structures
1634 describing it. */
1635 gsi = gsi_for_stmt (call);
1636 gsi_prev (&gsi);
1637 for (; !gsi_end_p (gsi); gsi_prev (&gsi))
1638 {
1639 struct ipa_known_agg_contents_list *n, **p;
1640 gimple *stmt = gsi_stmt (gsi);
1641 HOST_WIDE_INT lhs_offset, lhs_size, lhs_max_size;
1642 tree lhs, rhs, lhs_base;
1643 bool reverse;
1644
1645 if (!stmt_may_clobber_ref_p_1 (stmt, &r))
1646 continue;
1647 if (!gimple_assign_single_p (stmt))
1648 break;
1649
1650 lhs = gimple_assign_lhs (stmt);
1651 rhs = gimple_assign_rhs1 (stmt);
1652 if (!is_gimple_reg_type (TREE_TYPE (rhs))
1653 || TREE_CODE (lhs) == BIT_FIELD_REF
1654 || contains_bitfld_component_ref_p (lhs))
1655 break;
1656
1657 lhs_base = get_ref_base_and_extent (lhs, &lhs_offset, &lhs_size,
1658 &lhs_max_size, &reverse);
1659 if (lhs_max_size == -1
1660 || lhs_max_size != lhs_size)
1661 break;
1662
1663 if (check_ref)
1664 {
1665 if (TREE_CODE (lhs_base) != MEM_REF
1666 || TREE_OPERAND (lhs_base, 0) != arg_base
1667 || !integer_zerop (TREE_OPERAND (lhs_base, 1)))
1668 break;
1669 }
1670 else if (lhs_base != arg_base)
1671 {
1672 if (DECL_P (lhs_base))
1673 continue;
1674 else
1675 break;
1676 }
1677
1678 bool already_there = false;
1679 p = get_place_in_agg_contents_list (&list, lhs_offset, lhs_size,
1680 &already_there);
1681 if (!p)
1682 break;
1683 if (already_there)
1684 continue;
1685
1686 rhs = get_ssa_def_if_simple_copy (rhs);
1687 n = XALLOCA (struct ipa_known_agg_contents_list);
1688 n->size = lhs_size;
1689 n->offset = lhs_offset;
1690 if (is_gimple_ip_invariant (rhs))
1691 {
1692 n->constant = rhs;
1693 const_count++;
1694 }
1695 else
1696 n->constant = NULL_TREE;
1697 n->next = *p;
1698 *p = n;
1699
1700 item_count++;
1701 if (const_count == PARAM_VALUE (PARAM_IPA_MAX_AGG_ITEMS)
1702 || item_count == 2 * PARAM_VALUE (PARAM_IPA_MAX_AGG_ITEMS))
1703 break;
1704 }
1705
1706 /* Third stage just goes over the list and creates an appropriate vector of
1707 ipa_agg_jf_item structures out of it, of sourse only if there are
1708 any known constants to begin with. */
1709
1710 if (const_count)
1711 {
1712 jfunc->agg.by_ref = by_ref;
1713 build_agg_jump_func_from_list (list, const_count, arg_offset, jfunc);
1714 }
1715}
1716
1717/* Return the Ith param type of callee associated with call graph
1718 edge E. */
1719
1720tree
1721ipa_get_callee_param_type (struct cgraph_edge *e, int i)
1722{
1723 int n;
1724 tree type = (e->callee
1725 ? TREE_TYPE (e->callee->decl)
1726 : gimple_call_fntype (e->call_stmt));
1727 tree t = TYPE_ARG_TYPES (type);
1728
1729 for (n = 0; n < i; n++)
1730 {
1731 if (!t)
1732 break;
1733 t = TREE_CHAIN (t);
1734 }
1735 if (t)
1736 return TREE_VALUE (t);
1737 if (!e->callee)
1738 return NULL;
1739 t = DECL_ARGUMENTS (e->callee->decl);
1740 for (n = 0; n < i; n++)
1741 {
1742 if (!t)
1743 return NULL;
1744 t = TREE_CHAIN (t);
1745 }
1746 if (t)
1747 return TREE_TYPE (t);
1748 return NULL;
1749}

1751/* Return ipa_bits with VALUE and MASK values, which can be either a newly
1752 allocated structure or a previously existing one shared with other jump
1753 functions and/or transformation summaries. */
1754
1755ipa_bits *
1756ipa_get_ipa_bits_for_value (const widest_int &value, const widest_int &mask)
1757{
1758 ipa_bits tmp;
1759 tmp.value = value;
1760 tmp.mask = mask;
1761
1762 ipa_bits **slot = ipa_bits_hash_table->find_slot (&tmp, INSERT);
1763 if (*slot)
1764 return *slot;
1765
1766 ipa_bits *res = ggc_alloc<ipa_bits> ();
1767 res->value = value;
1768 res->mask = mask;
1769 *slot = res;
1770
1771 return res;
1772}

1774/* Assign to JF a pointer to ipa_bits structure with VALUE and MASK. Use hash
1775 table in order to avoid creating multiple same ipa_bits structures. */
1776
1777static void
1778ipa_set_jfunc_bits (ipa_jump_func *jf, const widest_int &value,
1779 const widest_int &mask)
1780{
1781 jf->bits = ipa_get_ipa_bits_for_value (value, mask);
1782}

1784/* Return a pointer to a value_range just like *TMP, but either find it in
1785 ipa_vr_hash_table or allocate it in GC memory. TMP->equiv must be NULL. */
1786
1787static value_range *
1788ipa_get_value_range (value_range *tmp)
1789{
1790 value_range **slot = ipa_vr_hash_table->find_slot (tmp, INSERT);
1791 if (*slot)
1792 return *slot;
1793
1794 value_range *vr = ggc_alloc<value_range> ();
1795 *vr = *tmp;
1796 *slot = vr;
1797
1798 return vr;
1799}

1802 equiv set. Use hash table in order to avoid creating multiple same copies of

1807{

1835
1836/* Compute jump function for all arguments of callsite CS and insert the
1837 information in the jump_functions array in the ipa_edge_args corresponding
1838 to this callsite. */
1839
1840static void
1841ipa_compute_jump_functions_for_edge (struct ipa_func_body_info *fbi,
1842 struct cgraph_edge *cs)
1843{
1844 struct ipa_node_params *info = IPA_NODE_REF (cs->caller);
1845 struct ipa_edge_args *args = IPA_EDGE_REF (cs);
1846 gcall *call = cs->call_stmt;
1847 int n, arg_num = gimple_call_num_args (call);
1848 bool useful_context = false;
1849
1850 if (arg_num == 0 || args->jump_functions)
1851 return;
1852 vec_safe_grow_cleared (args->jump_functions, arg_num);
1853 if (flag_devirtualize)
1854 vec_safe_grow_cleared (args->polymorphic_call_contexts, arg_num);
1855
1856 if (gimple_call_internal_p (call))
1857 return;
1858 if (ipa_func_spec_opts_forbid_analysis_p (cs->caller))
1859 return;
1860
1861 for (n = 0; n < arg_num; n++)
1862 {
1863 struct ipa_jump_func *jfunc = ipa_get_ith_jump_func (args, n);
1864 tree arg = gimple_call_arg (call, n);
1865 tree param_type = ipa_get_callee_param_type (cs, n);
1866 if (flag_devirtualize && POINTER_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (arg)))
1867 {
1868 tree instance;
1869 struct ipa_polymorphic_call_context context (cs->caller->decl,
1870 arg, cs->call_stmt,
1871 &instance);
1872 context.get_dynamic_type (instance, arg, NULL, cs->call_stmt);
1873 *ipa_get_ith_polymorhic_call_context (args, n) = context;
1874 if (!context.useless_p ())
1875 useful_context = true;
1876 }
1877
1878 if (POINTER_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (arg)))
1879 {
1880 bool addr_nonzero = false;
1881 bool strict_overflow = false;
1882
1883 if (TREE_CODE (arg) == SSA_NAME
1884 && param_type
1885 && get_ptr_nonnull (arg))
1886 addr_nonzero = true;
1887 else if (tree_single_nonzero_warnv_p (arg, &strict_overflow))
1888 addr_nonzero = true;
1889
1890 if (addr_nonzero)
1891 {
1892 tree z = build_int_cst (TREE_TYPE (arg), 0);
1893 ipa_set_jfunc_vr (jfunc, VR_ANTI_RANGE, z, z);
1894 }
1895 else
1896 gcc_assert (!jfunc->m_vr);
1897 }
1898 else
1899 {
1900 wide_int min, max;
1901 value_range_type type;
1902 if (TREE_CODE (arg) == SSA_NAME
1903 && param_type
1904 && (type = get_range_info (arg, &min, &max))
1905 && (type == VR_RANGE || type == VR_ANTI_RANGE))
1906 {
1907 value_range tmpvr,resvr;
1908
1909 tmpvr.type = type;
1910 tmpvr.min = wide_int_to_tree (TREE_TYPE (arg), min);
1911 tmpvr.max = wide_int_to_tree (TREE_TYPE (arg), max);
1912 tmpvr.equiv = NULL;
1913 memset (&resvr, 0, sizeof (resvr));
1914 extract_range_from_unary_expr (&resvr, NOP_EXPR, param_type,
1915 &tmpvr, TREE_TYPE (arg));
1916 if (resvr.type == VR_RANGE || resvr.type == VR_ANTI_RANGE)
1917 ipa_set_jfunc_vr (jfunc, &resvr);
1918 else
1919 gcc_assert (!jfunc->m_vr);
1920 }
1921 else
1922 gcc_assert (!jfunc->m_vr);
1923 }
1924
1925 if (INTEGRAL_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (arg))
1926 && (TREE_CODE (arg) == SSA_NAME || TREE_CODE (arg) == INTEGER_CST))
1927 {
1928 if (TREE_CODE (arg) == SSA_NAME)
1929 ipa_set_jfunc_bits (jfunc, 0,
1930 widest_int::from (get_nonzero_bits (arg),
1931 TYPE_SIGN (TREE_TYPE (arg))));
1932 else
1933 ipa_set_jfunc_bits (jfunc, wi::to_widest (arg), 0);
1934 }
1935 else if (POINTER_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (arg)))
1936 {
1937 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT bitpos;
1938 unsigned align;
1939
1940 get_pointer_alignment_1 (arg, &align, &bitpos);
1941 widest_int mask
1942 = wi::mask<widest_int>(TYPE_PRECISION (TREE_TYPE (arg)), false)
1943 .and_not (align / BITS_PER_UNIT - 1);
1944 widest_int value = bitpos / BITS_PER_UNIT;
1945 ipa_set_jfunc_bits (jfunc, value, mask);
1946 }
1947 else
1948 gcc_assert (!jfunc->bits);
1949
1950 if (is_gimple_ip_invariant (arg)
1951 || (VAR_P (arg)
1952 && is_global_var (arg)
1953 && TREE_READONLY (arg)))
1954 ipa_set_jf_constant (jfunc, arg, cs);
1955 else if (!is_gimple_reg_type (TREE_TYPE (arg))
1956 && TREE_CODE (arg) == PARM_DECL)
1957 {
1958 int index = ipa_get_param_decl_index (info, arg);
1959
1960 gcc_assert (index >=0);
1961 /* Aggregate passed by value, check for pass-through, otherwise we
1962 will attempt to fill in aggregate contents later in this
1963 for cycle. */
1964 if (parm_preserved_before_stmt_p (fbi, index, call, arg))
1965 {
1966 ipa_set_jf_simple_pass_through (jfunc, index, false);
1967 continue;
1968 }
1969 }
1970 else if (TREE_CODE (arg) == SSA_NAME)
1971 {
1972 if (SSA_NAME_IS_DEFAULT_DEF (arg))
1973 {
1974 int index = ipa_get_param_decl_index (info, SSA_NAME_VAR (arg));
1975 if (index >= 0)
1976 {
1977 bool agg_p;
1978 agg_p = parm_ref_data_pass_through_p (fbi, index, call, arg);
1979 ipa_set_jf_simple_pass_through (jfunc, index, agg_p);
1980 }
1981 }
1982 else
1983 {
1984 gimple *stmt = SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (arg);
1985 if (is_gimple_assign (stmt))
1986 compute_complex_assign_jump_func (fbi, info, jfunc,
1987 call, stmt, arg, param_type);
1988 else if (gimple_code (stmt) == GIMPLE_PHI)
1989 compute_complex_ancestor_jump_func (fbi, info, jfunc,
1990 call,
1991 as_a <gphi *> (stmt));
1992 }
1993 }
1994
1995 /* If ARG is pointer, we can not use its type to determine the type of aggregate
1996 passed (because type conversions are ignored in gimple). Usually we can
1997 safely get type from function declaration, but in case of K&R prototypes or
1998 variadic functions we can try our luck with type of the pointer passed.
1999 TODO: Since we look for actual initialization of the memory object, we may better
2000 work out the type based on the memory stores we find. */
2001 if (!param_type)
2002 param_type = TREE_TYPE (arg);
2003
2004 if ((jfunc->type != IPA_JF_PASS_THROUGH
2005 || !ipa_get_jf_pass_through_agg_preserved (jfunc))
2006 && (jfunc->type != IPA_JF_ANCESTOR
2007 || !ipa_get_jf_ancestor_agg_preserved (jfunc))
2008 && (AGGREGATE_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (arg))
2009 || POINTER_TYPE_P (param_type)))
2010 determine_locally_known_aggregate_parts (call, arg, param_type, jfunc);
2011 }
2012 if (!useful_context)
2013 vec_free (args->polymorphic_call_contexts);
2014}

2016/* Compute jump functions for all edges - both direct and indirect - outgoing
2017 from BB. */
2018
2019static void
2020ipa_compute_jump_functions_for_bb (struct ipa_func_body_info *fbi, basic_block bb)
2021{
2022 struct ipa_bb_info *bi = ipa_get_bb_info (fbi, bb);
2023 int i;
2024 struct cgraph_edge *cs;
2025
2026 FOR_EACH_VEC_ELT_REVERSE (bi->cg_edges, i, cs)
2027 {
2028 struct cgraph_node *callee = cs->callee;
2029
2030 if (callee)
2031 {
2032 callee->ultimate_alias_target ();
2033 /* We do not need to bother analyzing calls to unknown functions
2034 unless they may become known during lto/whopr. */
2035 if (!callee->definition && !flag_lto)
2036 continue;
2037 }
2038 ipa_compute_jump_functions_for_edge (fbi, cs);
2039 }
2040}
2041
2042/* If STMT looks like a statement loading a value from a member pointer formal
2043 parameter, return that parameter and store the offset of the field to
2044 *OFFSET_P, if it is non-NULL. Otherwise return NULL (but *OFFSET_P still
2045 might be clobbered). If USE_DELTA, then we look for a use of the delta
2046 field rather than the pfn. */
2047
2048static tree
2049ipa_get_stmt_member_ptr_load_param (gimple *stmt, bool use_delta,
2050 HOST_WIDE_INT *offset_p)
2051{
2052 tree rhs, rec, ref_field, ref_offset, fld, ptr_field, delta_field;
2053
2054 if (!gimple_assign_single_p (stmt))
2055 return NULL_TREE;
2056
2057 rhs = gimple_assign_rhs1 (stmt);
2058 if (TREE_CODE (rhs) == COMPONENT_REF)
2059 {
2060 ref_field = TREE_OPERAND (rhs, 1);
2061 rhs = TREE_OPERAND (rhs, 0);
2062 }
2063 else
2064 ref_field = NULL_TREE;
2065 if (TREE_CODE (rhs) != MEM_REF)
2066 return NULL_TREE;
2067 rec = TREE_OPERAND (rhs, 0);
2068 if (TREE_CODE (rec) != ADDR_EXPR)
2069 return NULL_TREE;
2070 rec = TREE_OPERAND (rec, 0);
2071 if (TREE_CODE (rec) != PARM_DECL
2072 || !type_like_member_ptr_p (TREE_TYPE (rec), &ptr_field, &delta_field))
2073 return NULL_TREE;
2074 ref_offset = TREE_OPERAND (rhs, 1);
2075
2076 if (use_delta)
2077 fld = delta_field;
2078 else
2079 fld = ptr_field;
2080 if (offset_p)
2081 *offset_p = int_bit_position (fld);
2082
2083 if (ref_field)
2084 {
2085 if (integer_nonzerop (ref_offset))
2086 return NULL_TREE;
2087 return ref_field == fld ? rec : NULL_TREE;
2088 }
2089 else
2090 return tree_int_cst_equal (byte_position (fld), ref_offset) ? rec
2091 : NULL_TREE;
2092}

2094/* Returns true iff T is an SSA_NAME defined by a statement. */

2096static bool
2097ipa_is_ssa_with_stmt_def (tree t)
2098{
2099 if (TREE_CODE (t) == SSA_NAME
2100 && !SSA_NAME_IS_DEFAULT_DEF (t))
2101 return true;
2102 else
2103 return false;
2104}

2106/* Find the indirect call graph edge corresponding to STMT and mark it as a
2107 call to a parameter number PARAM_INDEX. NODE is the caller. Return the
2108 indirect call graph edge. */
2109
2110static struct cgraph_edge *
2111ipa_note_param_call (struct cgraph_node *node, int param_index,
2112 gcall *stmt)
2113{
2114 struct cgraph_edge *cs;
2115
2116 cs = node->get_edge (stmt);
2117 cs->indirect_info->param_index = param_index;
2118 cs->indirect_info->agg_contents = 0;
2119 cs->indirect_info->member_ptr = 0;
2120 cs->indirect_info->guaranteed_unmodified = 0;
2121 return cs;
2122}

2124/* Analyze the CALL and examine uses of formal parameters of the caller NODE
2125 (described by INFO). PARMS_AINFO is a pointer to a vector containing
2126 intermediate information about each formal parameter. Currently it checks
2127 whether the call calls a pointer that is a formal parameter and if so, the
2128 parameter is marked with the called flag and an indirect call graph edge
2129 describing the call is created. This is very simple for ordinary pointers
2130 represented in SSA but not-so-nice when it comes to member pointers. The
2131 ugly part of this function does nothing more than trying to match the
2132 pattern of such a call. An example of such a pattern is the gimple dump
2133 below, the call is on the last line:
2134
2135 <bb 2>:
2136 f$__delta_5 = f.__delta;
2137 f$__pfn_24 = f.__pfn;
2138
2139 or
2140 <bb 2>:
2141 f$__delta_5 = MEM[(struct *)&f];
2142 f$__pfn_24 = MEM[(struct *)&f + 4B];
2143
2144 and a few lines below:
2145
2146 <bb 5>
2147 D.2496_3 = (int) f$__pfn_24;
2148 D.2497_4 = D.2496_3 & 1;
2149 if (D.2497_4 != 0)
2150 goto <bb 3>;
2151 else
2152 goto <bb 4>;
2153
2154 <bb 6>:
2155 D.2500_7 = (unsigned int) f$__delta_5;
2156 D.2501_8 = &S + D.2500_7;
2157 D.2502_9 = (int (*__vtbl_ptr_type) (void) * *) D.2501_8;
2158 D.2503_10 = *D.2502_9;
2159 D.2504_12 = f$__pfn_24 + -1;
2160 D.2505_13 = (unsigned int) D.2504_12;
2161 D.2506_14 = D.2503_10 + D.2505_13;
2162 D.2507_15 = *D.2506_14;
2163 iftmp.11_16 = (String:: *) D.2507_15;
2164
2165 <bb 7>:
2166 # iftmp.11_1 = PHI <iftmp.11_16(3), f$__pfn_24(2)>
2167 D.2500_19 = (unsigned int) f$__delta_5;
2168 D.2508_20 = &S + D.2500_19;
2169 D.2493_21 = iftmp.11_1 (D.2508_20, 4);
2170
2171 Such patterns are results of simple calls to a member pointer:
2172
2173 int doprinting (int (MyString::* f)(int) const)
2174 {
2175 MyString S ("somestring");
2176
2177 return (S.*f)(4);
2178 }
2179
2180 Moreover, the function also looks for called pointers loaded from aggregates
2181 passed by value or reference. */
2182
2183static void
2184ipa_analyze_indirect_call_uses (struct ipa_func_body_info *fbi, gcall *call,
2185 tree target)
2186{
2187 struct ipa_node_params *info = fbi->info;
2188 HOST_WIDE_INT offset;
2189 bool by_ref;
2190
2191 if (SSA_NAME_IS_DEFAULT_DEF (target))
2192 {
2193 tree var = SSA_NAME_VAR (target);
2194 int index = ipa_get_param_decl_index (info, var);
2195 if (index >= 0)
2196 ipa_note_param_call (fbi->node, index, call);
2197 return;
2198 }
2199
2200 int index;
2201 gimple *def = SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (target);
2202 bool guaranteed_unmodified;
2203 if (gimple_assign_single_p (def)
2204 && ipa_load_from_parm_agg (fbi, info->descriptors, def,
2205 gimple_assign_rhs1 (def), &index, &offset,
2206 NULL, &by_ref, &guaranteed_unmodified))
2207 {
2208 struct cgraph_edge *cs = ipa_note_param_call (fbi->node, index, call);
2209 cs->indirect_info->offset = offset;
2210 cs->indirect_info->agg_contents = 1;
2211 cs->indirect_info->by_ref = by_ref;
2212 cs->indirect_info->guaranteed_unmodified = guaranteed_unmodified;
2213 return;
2214 }
2215
2216 /* Now we need to try to match the complex pattern of calling a member
2217 pointer. */
2218 if (gimple_code (def) != GIMPLE_PHI
2219 || gimple_phi_num_args (def) != 2
2220 || !POINTER_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (target))
2221 || TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (TREE_TYPE (target))) != METHOD_TYPE)
2222 return;
2223
2224 /* First, we need to check whether one of these is a load from a member
2225 pointer that is a parameter to this function. */
2226 tree n1 = PHI_ARG_DEF (def, 0);
2227 tree n2 = PHI_ARG_DEF (def, 1);
2228 if (!ipa_is_ssa_with_stmt_def (n1) || !ipa_is_ssa_with_stmt_def (n2))
2229 return;
2230 gimple *d1 = SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (n1);
2231 gimple *d2 = SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (n2);
2232
2233 tree rec;
2234 basic_block bb, virt_bb;
2235 basic_block join = gimple_bb (def);
2236 if ((rec = ipa_get_stmt_member_ptr_load_param (d1, false, &offset)))
2237 {
2238 if (ipa_get_stmt_member_ptr_load_param (d2, false, NULL))
2239 return;
2240
2241 bb = EDGE_PRED (join, 0)->src;
2242 virt_bb = gimple_bb (d2);
2243 }
2244 else if ((rec = ipa_get_stmt_member_ptr_load_param (d2, false, &offset)))
2245 {
2246 bb = EDGE_PRED (join, 1)->src;
2247 virt_bb = gimple_bb (d1);
2248 }
2249 else
2250 return;
2251
2252 /* Second, we need to check that the basic blocks are laid out in the way
2253 corresponding to the pattern. */
2254
2255 if (!single_pred_p (virt_bb) || !single_succ_p (virt_bb)
2256 || single_pred (virt_bb) != bb
2257 || single_succ (virt_bb) != join)
2258 return;
2259
2260 /* Third, let's see that the branching is done depending on the least
2261 significant bit of the pfn. */
2262
2263 gimple *branch = last_stmt (bb);
2264 if (!branch || gimple_code (branch) != GIMPLE_COND)
2265 return;
2266
2267 if ((gimple_cond_code (branch) != NE_EXPR
2268 && gimple_cond_code (branch) != EQ_EXPR)
2269 || !integer_zerop (gimple_cond_rhs (branch)))
2270 return;
2271
2272 tree cond = gimple_cond_lhs (branch);
2273 if (!ipa_is_ssa_with_stmt_def (cond))
2274 return;
2275
2276 def = SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (cond);
2277 if (!is_gimple_assign (def)
2278 || gimple_assign_rhs_code (def) != BIT_AND_EXPR
2279 || !integer_onep (gimple_assign_rhs2 (def)))
2280 return;
2281
2282 cond = gimple_assign_rhs1 (def);
2283 if (!ipa_is_ssa_with_stmt_def (cond))
2284 return;
2285
2286 def = SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (cond);
2287
2288 if (is_gimple_assign (def)
2289 && CONVERT_EXPR_CODE_P (gimple_assign_rhs_code (def)))
2290 {
2291 cond = gimple_assign_rhs1 (def);
2292 if (!ipa_is_ssa_with_stmt_def (cond))
2293 return;
2294 def = SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (cond);
2295 }
2296
2297 tree rec2;
2298 rec2 = ipa_get_stmt_member_ptr_load_param (def,
2299 (TARGET_PTRMEMFUNC_VBIT_LOCATION
2300 == ptrmemfunc_vbit_in_delta),
2301 NULL);
2302 if (rec != rec2)
2303 return;
2304
2305 index = ipa_get_param_decl_index (info, rec);
2306 if (index >= 0
2307 && parm_preserved_before_stmt_p (fbi, index, call, rec))
2308 {
2309 struct cgraph_edge *cs = ipa_note_param_call (fbi->node, index, call);
2310 cs->indirect_info->offset = offset;
2311 cs->indirect_info->agg_contents = 1;
2312 cs->indirect_info->member_ptr = 1;
2313 cs->indirect_info->guaranteed_unmodified = 1;
2314 }
2315
2316 return;
2317}

2319/* Analyze a CALL to an OBJ_TYPE_REF which is passed in TARGET and if the
2320 object referenced in the expression is a formal parameter of the caller
2321 FBI->node (described by FBI->info), create a call note for the
2322 statement. */
2323
2324static void
2325ipa_analyze_virtual_call_uses (struct ipa_func_body_info *fbi,
2326 gcall *call, tree target)
2327{
2328 tree obj = OBJ_TYPE_REF_OBJECT (target);
2329 int index;
2330 HOST_WIDE_INT anc_offset;
2331
2332 if (!flag_devirtualize)
2333 return;
2334
2335 if (TREE_CODE (obj) != SSA_NAME)
2336 return;
2337
2338 struct ipa_node_params *info = fbi->info;
2339 if (SSA_NAME_IS_DEFAULT_DEF (obj))
2340 {
2341 struct ipa_jump_func jfunc;
2342 if (TREE_CODE (SSA_NAME_VAR (obj)) != PARM_DECL)
2343 return;
2344
2345 anc_offset = 0;
2346 index = ipa_get_param_decl_index (info, SSA_NAME_VAR (obj));
2347 gcc_assert (index >= 0);
2348 if (detect_type_change_ssa (obj, obj_type_ref_class (target),
2349 call, &jfunc))
2350 return;
2351 }
2352 else
2353 {
2354 struct ipa_jump_func jfunc;
2355 gimple *stmt = SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (obj);
2356 tree expr;
2357
2358 expr = get_ancestor_addr_info (stmt, &obj, &anc_offset);
2359 if (!expr)
2360 return;
2361 index = ipa_get_param_decl_index (info,
2362 SSA_NAME_VAR (TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0)));
2363 gcc_assert (index >= 0);
2364 if (detect_type_change (obj, expr, obj_type_ref_class (target),
2365 call, &jfunc, anc_offset))
2366 return;
2367 }
2368
2369 struct cgraph_edge *cs = ipa_note_param_call (fbi->node, index, call);
2370 struct cgraph_indirect_call_info *ii = cs->indirect_info;
2371 ii->offset = anc_offset;
2372 ii->otr_token = tree_to_uhwi (OBJ_TYPE_REF_TOKEN (target));
2373 ii->otr_type = obj_type_ref_class (target);
2374 ii->polymorphic = 1;
2375}
2376
2377/* Analyze a call statement CALL whether and how it utilizes formal parameters
2378 of the caller (described by INFO). PARMS_AINFO is a pointer to a vector
2379 containing intermediate information about each formal parameter. */
2380
2381static void
2382ipa_analyze_call_uses (struct ipa_func_body_info *fbi, gcall *call)
2383{
2384 tree target = gimple_call_fn (call);
2385
2386 if (!target
2387 || (TREE_CODE (target) != SSA_NAME
2388 && !virtual_method_call_p (target)))
2389 return;
2390
2391 struct cgraph_edge *cs = fbi->node->get_edge (call);
2392 /* If we previously turned the call into a direct call, there is
2393 no need to analyze. */
2394 if (cs && !cs->indirect_unknown_callee)
2395 return;
2396
2397 if (cs->indirect_info->polymorphic && flag_devirtualize)
2398 {
2399 tree instance;
2400 tree target = gimple_call_fn (call);
2401 ipa_polymorphic_call_context context (current_function_decl,
2402 target, call, &instance);
2403
2404 gcc_checking_assert (cs->indirect_info->otr_type
2405 == obj_type_ref_class (target));
2406 gcc_checking_assert (cs->indirect_info->otr_token
2407 == tree_to_shwi (OBJ_TYPE_REF_TOKEN (target)));
2408
2409 cs->indirect_info->vptr_changed
2410 = !context.get_dynamic_type (instance,
2411 OBJ_TYPE_REF_OBJECT (target),
2412 obj_type_ref_class (target), call);
2413 cs->indirect_info->context = context;
2414 }
2415
2416 if (TREE_CODE (target) == SSA_NAME)
2417 ipa_analyze_indirect_call_uses (fbi, call, target);
2418 else if (virtual_method_call_p (target))
2419 ipa_analyze_virtual_call_uses (fbi, call, target);
2420}

2423/* Analyze the call statement STMT with respect to formal parameters (described
2424 in INFO) of caller given by FBI->NODE. Currently it only checks whether
2425 formal parameters are called. */

2427static void
2428ipa_analyze_stmt_uses (struct ipa_func_body_info *fbi, gimple *stmt)

2434/* Callback of walk_stmt_load_store_addr_ops for the visit_load.
2435 If OP is a parameter declaration, mark it as used in the info structure
2436 passed in DATA. */
2437
2438static bool
2439visit_ref_for_mod_analysis (gimple *, tree op, tree, void *data)
2440{
2441 struct ipa_node_params *info = (struct ipa_node_params *) data;
2442
2443 op = get_base_address (op);
2444 if (op
2445 && TREE_CODE (op) == PARM_DECL)
2446 {
2447 int index = ipa_get_param_decl_index (info, op);
2448 gcc_assert (index >= 0);
2449 ipa_set_param_used (info, index, true);
2450 }
2451
2452 return false;
2453}

2455/* Scan the statements in BB and inspect the uses of formal parameters. Store
2456 the findings in various structures of the associated ipa_node_params
2457 structure, such as parameter flags, notes etc. FBI holds various data about
2458 the function being analyzed. */
2459
2460static void
2461ipa_analyze_params_uses_in_bb (struct ipa_func_body_info *fbi, basic_block bb)
2462{
2463 gimple_stmt_iterator gsi;
2464 for (gsi = gsi_start_bb (bb); !gsi_end_p (gsi); gsi_next (&gsi))
2465 {
2466 gimple *stmt = gsi_stmt (gsi);
2467
2468 if (is_gimple_debug (stmt))
2469 continue;
2470
2471 ipa_analyze_stmt_uses (fbi, stmt);
2472 walk_stmt_load_store_addr_ops (stmt, fbi->info,
2473 visit_ref_for_mod_analysis,
2474 visit_ref_for_mod_analysis,
2475 visit_ref_for_mod_analysis);
2476 }
2477 for (gsi = gsi_start_phis (bb); !gsi_end_p (gsi); gsi_next (&gsi))
2478 walk_stmt_load_store_addr_ops (gsi_stmt (gsi), fbi->info,
2479 visit_ref_for_mod_analysis,
2480 visit_ref_for_mod_analysis,
2481 visit_ref_for_mod_analysis);
2482}

2484/* Calculate controlled uses of parameters of NODE. */
2485
2486static void
2487ipa_analyze_controlled_uses (struct cgraph_node *node)
2488{
2489 struct ipa_node_params *info = IPA_NODE_REF (node);
2490
2491 for (int i = 0; i < ipa_get_param_count (info); i++)
2492 {
2493 tree parm = ipa_get_param (info, i);
2494 int controlled_uses = 0;
2495
2496 /* For SSA regs see if parameter is used. For non-SSA we compute
2497 the flag during modification analysis. */
2498 if (is_gimple_reg (parm))
2499 {
2500 tree ddef = ssa_default_def (DECL_STRUCT_FUNCTION (node->decl),
2501 parm);
2502 if (ddef && !has_zero_uses (ddef))
2503 {
2504 imm_use_iterator imm_iter;
2505 use_operand_p use_p;
2506
2507 ipa_set_param_used (info, i, true);
2508 FOR_EACH_IMM_USE_FAST (use_p, imm_iter, ddef)
2509 if (!is_gimple_call (USE_STMT (use_p)))
2510 {
2511 if (!is_gimple_debug (USE_STMT (use_p)))
2512 {
2513 controlled_uses = IPA_UNDESCRIBED_USE;
2514 break;
2515 }
2516 }
2517 else
2518 controlled_uses++;
2519 }
2520 else
2521 controlled_uses = 0;
2522 }
2523 else
2524 controlled_uses = IPA_UNDESCRIBED_USE;
2525 ipa_set_controlled_uses (info, i, controlled_uses);
2526 }
2527}

2573/* Initialize the array describing properties of formal parameters
2574 of NODE, analyze their uses and compute jump functions associated
2575 with actual arguments of calls from within NODE. */
2576
2577void
2578ipa_analyze_node (struct cgraph_node *node)
2579{
2580 struct ipa_func_body_info fbi;
2581 struct ipa_node_params *info;
2582
2583 ipa_check_create_node_params ();
2584 ipa_check_create_edge_args ();
2585 info = IPA_NODE_REF (node);
2586
2587 if (info->analysis_done)
2588 return;
2589 info->analysis_done = 1;
2590
2591 if (ipa_func_spec_opts_forbid_analysis_p (node))
2592 {
2593 for (int i = 0; i < ipa_get_param_count (info); i++)
2594 {
2595 ipa_set_param_used (info, i, true);
2596 ipa_set_controlled_uses (info, i, IPA_UNDESCRIBED_USE);
2597 }
2598 return;
2599 }
2600
2601 struct function *func = DECL_STRUCT_FUNCTION (node->decl);
2602 push_cfun (func);
2603 calculate_dominance_info (CDI_DOMINATORS);
2604 ipa_initialize_node_params (node);
2605 ipa_analyze_controlled_uses (node);
2606
2607 fbi.node = node;
2608 fbi.info = IPA_NODE_REF (node);
2609 fbi.bb_infos = vNULL;
2610 fbi.bb_infos.safe_grow_cleared (last_basic_block_for_fn (cfun));
2611 fbi.param_count = ipa_get_param_count (info);
2612 fbi.aa_walked = 0;
2613
2614 for (struct cgraph_edge *cs = node->callees; cs; cs = cs->next_callee)
2615 {
2616 ipa_bb_info *bi = ipa_get_bb_info (&fbi, gimple_bb (cs->call_stmt));
2617 bi->cg_edges.safe_push (cs);
2618 }
2619
2620 for (struct cgraph_edge *cs = node->indirect_calls; cs; cs = cs->next_callee)
2621 {
2622 ipa_bb_info *bi = ipa_get_bb_info (&fbi, gimple_bb (cs->call_stmt));
2623 bi->cg_edges.safe_push (cs);
2624 }
2625
2626 analysis_dom_walker (&fbi).walk (ENTRY_BLOCK_PTR_FOR_FN (cfun));
2627
2628 ipa_release_body_info (&fbi);
2629 free_dominance_info (CDI_DOMINATORS);
2630 pop_cfun ();
2631}

2633/* Update the jump functions associated with call graph edge E when the call
2634 graph edge CS is being inlined, assuming that E->caller is already (possibly
2635 indirectly) inlined into CS->callee and that E has not been inlined. */
2636
2637static void
2638update_jump_functions_after_inlining (struct cgraph_edge *cs,
2639 struct cgraph_edge *e)
2640{
2641 struct ipa_edge_args *top = IPA_EDGE_REF (cs);
2642 struct ipa_edge_args *args = IPA_EDGE_REF (e);
2643 int count = ipa_get_cs_argument_count (args);
2644 int i;
2645
2646 for (i = 0; i < count; i++)
2647 {
2648 struct ipa_jump_func *dst = ipa_get_ith_jump_func (args, i);
2649 struct ipa_polymorphic_call_context *dst_ctx
2650 = ipa_get_ith_polymorhic_call_context (args, i);
2651
2652 if (dst->type == IPA_JF_ANCESTOR)
2653 {
2654 struct ipa_jump_func *src;
2655 int dst_fid = dst->value.ancestor.formal_id;
2656 struct ipa_polymorphic_call_context *src_ctx
2657 = ipa_get_ith_polymorhic_call_context (top, dst_fid);
2658
2659 /* Variable number of arguments can cause havoc if we try to access
2660 one that does not exist in the inlined edge. So make sure we
2661 don't. */
2662 if (dst_fid >= ipa_get_cs_argument_count (top))
2663 {
2664 ipa_set_jf_unknown (dst);
2665 continue;
2666 }
2667
2668 src = ipa_get_ith_jump_func (top, dst_fid);
2669
2670 if (src_ctx && !src_ctx->useless_p ())
2671 {
2672 struct ipa_polymorphic_call_context ctx = *src_ctx;
2673
2674 /* TODO: Make type preserved safe WRT contexts. */
2675 if (!ipa_get_jf_ancestor_type_preserved (dst))
2676 ctx.possible_dynamic_type_change (e->in_polymorphic_cdtor);
2677 ctx.offset_by (dst->value.ancestor.offset);
2678 if (!ctx.useless_p ())
2679 {
2680 if (!dst_ctx)
2681 {
2682 vec_safe_grow_cleared (args->polymorphic_call_contexts,
2683 count);
2684 dst_ctx = ipa_get_ith_polymorhic_call_context (args, i);
2685 }
2686
2687 dst_ctx->combine_with (ctx);
2688 }
2689 }
2690
2691 if (src->agg.items
2692 && (dst->value.ancestor.agg_preserved || !src->agg.by_ref))
2693 {
2694 struct ipa_agg_jf_item *item;
2695 int j;
2696
2697 /* Currently we do not produce clobber aggregate jump functions,
2698 replace with merging when we do. */
2699 gcc_assert (!dst->agg.items);
2700
2701 dst->agg.items = vec_safe_copy (src->agg.items);
2702 dst->agg.by_ref = src->agg.by_ref;
2703 FOR_EACH_VEC_SAFE_ELT (dst->agg.items, j, item)
2704 item->offset -= dst->value.ancestor.offset;
2705 }
2706
2707 if (src->type == IPA_JF_PASS_THROUGH
2708 && src->value.pass_through.operation == NOP_EXPR)
2709 {
2710 dst->value.ancestor.formal_id = src->value.pass_through.formal_id;
2711 dst->value.ancestor.agg_preserved &=
2712 src->value.pass_through.agg_preserved;
2713 }
2714 else if (src->type == IPA_JF_PASS_THROUGH
2715 && TREE_CODE_CLASS (src->value.pass_through.operation) == tcc_unary)
2716 {
2717 dst->value.ancestor.formal_id = src->value.pass_through.formal_id;
2718 dst->value.ancestor.agg_preserved = false;
2719 }
2720 else if (src->type == IPA_JF_ANCESTOR)
2721 {
2722 dst->value.ancestor.formal_id = src->value.ancestor.formal_id;
2723 dst->value.ancestor.offset += src->value.ancestor.offset;
2724 dst->value.ancestor.agg_preserved &=
2725 src->value.ancestor.agg_preserved;
2726 }
2727 else
2728 ipa_set_jf_unknown (dst);
2729 }
2730 else if (dst->type == IPA_JF_PASS_THROUGH)
2731 {
2732 struct ipa_jump_func *src;
2733 /* We must check range due to calls with variable number of arguments
2734 and we cannot combine jump functions with operations. */
2735 if (dst->value.pass_through.operation == NOP_EXPR
2736 && (dst->value.pass_through.formal_id
2737 < ipa_get_cs_argument_count (top)))
2738 {
2739 int dst_fid = dst->value.pass_through.formal_id;
2740 src = ipa_get_ith_jump_func (top, dst_fid);
2741 bool dst_agg_p = ipa_get_jf_pass_through_agg_preserved (dst);
2742 struct ipa_polymorphic_call_context *src_ctx
2743 = ipa_get_ith_polymorhic_call_context (top, dst_fid);
2744
2745 if (src_ctx && !src_ctx->useless_p ())
2746 {
2747 struct ipa_polymorphic_call_context ctx = *src_ctx;
2748
2749 /* TODO: Make type preserved safe WRT contexts. */
2750 if (!ipa_get_jf_pass_through_type_preserved (dst))
2751 ctx.possible_dynamic_type_change (e->in_polymorphic_cdtor);
2752 if (!ctx.useless_p ())
2753 {
2754 if (!dst_ctx)
2755 {
2756 vec_safe_grow_cleared (args->polymorphic_call_contexts,
2757 count);
2758 dst_ctx = ipa_get_ith_polymorhic_call_context (args, i);
2759 }
2760 dst_ctx->combine_with (ctx);
2761 }
2762 }
2763 switch (src->type)
2764 {
2765 case IPA_JF_UNKNOWN:
2766 ipa_set_jf_unknown (dst);
2767 break;
2768 case IPA_JF_CONST:
2769 ipa_set_jf_cst_copy (dst, src);
2770 break;
2771
2772 case IPA_JF_PASS_THROUGH:
2773 {
2774 int formal_id = ipa_get_jf_pass_through_formal_id (src);
2775 enum tree_code operation;
2776 operation = ipa_get_jf_pass_through_operation (src);
2777
2778 if (operation == NOP_EXPR)
2779 {
2780 bool agg_p;
2781 agg_p = dst_agg_p
2782 && ipa_get_jf_pass_through_agg_preserved (src);
2783 ipa_set_jf_simple_pass_through (dst, formal_id, agg_p);
2784 }
2785 else if (TREE_CODE_CLASS (operation) == tcc_unary)
2786 ipa_set_jf_unary_pass_through (dst, formal_id, operation);
2787 else
2788 {
2789 tree operand = ipa_get_jf_pass_through_operand (src);
2790 ipa_set_jf_arith_pass_through (dst, formal_id, operand,
2791 operation);
2792 }
2793 break;
2794 }
2795 case IPA_JF_ANCESTOR:
2796 {
2797 bool agg_p;
2798 agg_p = dst_agg_p
2799 && ipa_get_jf_ancestor_agg_preserved (src);
2800 ipa_set_ancestor_jf (dst,
2801 ipa_get_jf_ancestor_offset (src),
2802 ipa_get_jf_ancestor_formal_id (src),
2803 agg_p);
2804 break;
2805 }
2806 default:
2807 gcc_unreachable ();
2808 }
2809
2810 if (src->agg.items
2811 && (dst_agg_p || !src->agg.by_ref))
2812 {
2813 /* Currently we do not produce clobber aggregate jump
2814 functions, replace with merging when we do. */
2815 gcc_assert (!dst->agg.items);
2816
2817 dst->agg.by_ref = src->agg.by_ref;
2818 dst->agg.items = vec_safe_copy (src->agg.items);
2819 }
2820 }
2821 else
2822 ipa_set_jf_unknown (dst);
2823 }
2824 }
2825}
