2827/* If TARGET is an addr_expr of a function declaration, make it the
2828 (SPECULATIVE)destination of an indirect edge IE and return the edge.
2829 Otherwise, return NULL. */
2830
2831struct cgraph_edge *
2832ipa_make_edge_direct_to_target (struct cgraph_edge *ie, tree target,
2833 bool speculative)
2834{
2835 struct cgraph_node *callee;
2836 struct inline_edge_summary *es = inline_edge_summary (ie);
2837 bool unreachable = false;
2838
2839 if (TREE_CODE (target) == ADDR_EXPR)
2840 target = TREE_OPERAND (target, 0);
2841 if (TREE_CODE (target) != FUNCTION_DECL)
2842 {
2843 target = canonicalize_constructor_val (target, NULL);
2844 if (!target || TREE_CODE (target) != FUNCTION_DECL)
2845 {
2846 /* Member pointer call that goes through a VMT lookup. */
2847 if (ie->indirect_info->member_ptr
2848 /* Or if target is not an invariant expression and we do not
2849 know if it will evaulate to function at runtime.
2850 This can happen when folding through &VAR, where &VAR
2851 is IP invariant, but VAR itself is not.
2852
2853 TODO: Revisit this when GCC 5 is branched. It seems that
2854 member_ptr check is not needed and that we may try to fold
2855 the expression and see if VAR is readonly. */
2856 || !is_gimple_ip_invariant (target))
2857 {
2858 if (dump_enabled_p ())
2859 {
2860 location_t loc = gimple_location_safe (ie->call_stmt);
2861 dump_printf_loc (MSG_OPTIMIZED_LOCATIONS, loc,
2862 "discovered direct call non-invariant "
2863 "%s/%i\n",
2864 ie->caller->name (), ie->caller->order);
2865 }
2866 return NULL;
2867 }
2868
2869
2870 if (dump_enabled_p ())
2871 {
2872 location_t loc = gimple_location_safe (ie->call_stmt);
2873 dump_printf_loc (MSG_OPTIMIZED_LOCATIONS, loc,
2874 "discovered direct call to non-function in %s/%i, "
2875 "making it __builtin_unreachable\n",
2876 ie->caller->name (), ie->caller->order);
2877 }
2878
2879 target = builtin_decl_implicit (BUILT_IN_UNREACHABLE);
2880 callee = cgraph_node::get_create (target);
2881 unreachable = true;
2882 }
2883 else
2884 callee = cgraph_node::get (target);
2885 }
2886 else
2887 callee = cgraph_node::get (target);
2888
2889 /* Because may-edges are not explicitely represented and vtable may be external,
2890 we may create the first reference to the object in the unit. */
2891 if (!callee || callee->global.inlined_to)
2892 {
2893
2894 /* We are better to ensure we can refer to it.
2895 In the case of static functions we are out of luck, since we already
2896 removed its body. In the case of public functions we may or may
2897 not introduce the reference. */
2898 if (!canonicalize_constructor_val (target, NULL)
2899 || !TREE_PUBLIC (target))
2900 {
2901 if (dump_file)
2902 fprintf (dump_file, "ipa-prop: Discovered call to a known target "
2903 "(%s/%i -> %s/%i) but can not refer to it. Giving up.\n",
2904 xstrdup_for_dump (ie->caller->name ()),
2905 ie->caller->order,
2906 xstrdup_for_dump (ie->callee->name ()),
2907 ie->callee->order);
2908 return NULL;
2909 }
2910 callee = cgraph_node::get_create (target);
2911 }
2912
2913 /* If the edge is already speculated. */
2914 if (speculative && ie->speculative)
2915 {
2916 struct cgraph_edge *e2;
2917 struct ipa_ref *ref;
2918 ie->speculative_call_info (e2, ie, ref);
2919 if (e2->callee->ultimate_alias_target ()
2920 != callee->ultimate_alias_target ())
2921 {
2922 if (dump_file)
2923 fprintf (dump_file, "ipa-prop: Discovered call to a speculative target "
2924 "(%s/%i -> %s/%i) but the call is already speculated to %s/%i. Giving up.\n",
2925 xstrdup_for_dump (ie->caller->name ()),
2926 ie->caller->order,
2927 xstrdup_for_dump (callee->name ()),
2928 callee->order,
2929 xstrdup_for_dump (e2->callee->name ()),
2930 e2->callee->order);
2931 }
2932 else
2933 {
2934 if (dump_file)
2935 fprintf (dump_file, "ipa-prop: Discovered call to a speculative target "
2936 "(%s/%i -> %s/%i) this agree with previous speculation.\n",
2937 xstrdup_for_dump (ie->caller->name ()),
2938 ie->caller->order,
2939 xstrdup_for_dump (callee->name ()),
2940 callee->order);
2941 }
2942 return NULL;
2943 }
2944
2945 if (!dbg_cnt (devirt))
2946 return NULL;
2947
2948 ipa_check_create_node_params ();
2949
2950 /* We can not make edges to inline clones. It is bug that someone removed
2951 the cgraph node too early. */
2952 gcc_assert (!callee->global.inlined_to);
2953
2954 if (dump_file && !unreachable)
2955 {
2956 fprintf (dump_file, "ipa-prop: Discovered %s call to a %s target "
2957 "(%s/%i -> %s/%i), for stmt ",
2958 ie->indirect_info->polymorphic ? "a virtual" : "an indirect",
2959 speculative ? "speculative" : "known",
2960 xstrdup_for_dump (ie->caller->name ()),
2961 ie->caller->order,
2962 xstrdup_for_dump (callee->name ()),
2963 callee->order);
2964 if (ie->call_stmt)
2965 print_gimple_stmt (dump_file, ie->call_stmt, 2, TDF_SLIM);
2966 else
2967 fprintf (dump_file, "with uid %i\n", ie->lto_stmt_uid);
2968 }
2969 if (dump_enabled_p ())
2970 {
2971 location_t loc = gimple_location_safe (ie->call_stmt);
2972
2973 dump_printf_loc (MSG_OPTIMIZED_LOCATIONS, loc,
2974 "converting indirect call in %s to direct call to %s\n",
2975 ie->caller->name (), callee->name ());
2976 }
2977 if (!speculative)
2978 {
2979 struct cgraph_edge *orig = ie;
2980 ie = ie->make_direct (callee);
2981 /* If we resolved speculative edge the cost is already up to date
2982 for direct call (adjusted by inline_edge_duplication_hook). */
2983 if (ie == orig)
2984 {
2985 es = inline_edge_summary (ie);
2986 es->call_stmt_size -= (eni_size_weights.indirect_call_cost
2987 - eni_size_weights.call_cost);
2988 es->call_stmt_time -= (eni_time_weights.indirect_call_cost
2989 - eni_time_weights.call_cost);
2990 }
2991 }
2992 else
2993 {
2994 if (!callee->can_be_discarded_p ())
2995 {
2996 cgraph_node *alias;
2997 alias = dyn_cast<cgraph_node *> (callee->noninterposable_alias ());
2998 if (alias)
2999 callee = alias;
3000 }
3001 /* make_speculative will update ie's cost to direct call cost. */
3002 ie = ie->make_speculative
3003 (callee, ie->count * 8 / 10, ie->frequency * 8 / 10);
3004 }
3005
3006 return ie;
3007}

3009/* Attempt to locate an interprocedural constant at a given REQ_OFFSET in
3010 CONSTRUCTOR and return it. Return NULL if the search fails for some
3011 reason. */
3012
3013static tree
3014find_constructor_constant_at_offset (tree constructor, HOST_WIDE_INT req_offset)
3015{
3016 tree type = TREE_TYPE (constructor);
3017 if (TREE_CODE (type) != ARRAY_TYPE
3018 && TREE_CODE (type) != RECORD_TYPE)
3019 return NULL;
3020
3021 unsigned ix;
3022 tree index, val;
3023 FOR_EACH_CONSTRUCTOR_ELT (CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (constructor), ix, index, val)
3024 {
3025 HOST_WIDE_INT elt_offset;
3026 if (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE)
3027 {
3028 offset_int off;
3029 tree unit_size = TYPE_SIZE_UNIT (TREE_TYPE (type));
3030 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (unit_size) == INTEGER_CST);
3031
3032 if (index)
3033 {
3034 if (TREE_CODE (index) == RANGE_EXPR)
3035 off = wi::to_offset (TREE_OPERAND (index, 0));
3036 else
3037 off = wi::to_offset (index);
3038 if (TYPE_DOMAIN (type) && TYPE_MIN_VALUE (TYPE_DOMAIN (type)))
3039 {
3040 tree low_bound = TYPE_MIN_VALUE (TYPE_DOMAIN (type));
3041 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (unit_size) == INTEGER_CST);
3042 off = wi::sext (off - wi::to_offset (low_bound),
3043 TYPE_PRECISION (TREE_TYPE (index)));
3044 }
3045 off *= wi::to_offset (unit_size);
3046 /* ??? Handle more than just the first index of a
3047 RANGE_EXPR. */
3048 }
3049 else
3050 off = wi::to_offset (unit_size) * ix;
3051
3052 off = wi::lshift (off, LOG2_BITS_PER_UNIT);
3053 if (!wi::fits_shwi_p (off) || wi::neg_p (off))
3054 continue;
3055 elt_offset = off.to_shwi ();
3056 }
3057 else if (TREE_CODE (type) == RECORD_TYPE)
3058 {
3059 gcc_checking_assert (index && TREE_CODE (index) == FIELD_DECL);
3060 if (DECL_BIT_FIELD (index))
3061 continue;
3062 elt_offset = int_bit_position (index);
3063 }
3064 else
3065 gcc_unreachable ();
3066
3067 if (elt_offset > req_offset)
3068 return NULL;
3069
3070 if (TREE_CODE (val) == CONSTRUCTOR)
3071 return find_constructor_constant_at_offset (val,
3072 req_offset - elt_offset);
3073
3074 if (elt_offset == req_offset
3075 && is_gimple_reg_type (TREE_TYPE (val))
3076 && is_gimple_ip_invariant (val))
3077 return val;
3078 }
3079 return NULL;
3080}

3082/* Check whether SCALAR could be used to look up an aggregate interprocedural
3083 invariant from a static constructor and if so, return it. Otherwise return
3084 NULL. */
3085
3086static tree
3087ipa_find_agg_cst_from_init (tree scalar, HOST_WIDE_INT offset, bool by_ref)
3088{
3089 if (by_ref)
3090 {
3091 if (TREE_CODE (scalar) != ADDR_EXPR)
3092 return NULL;
3093 scalar = TREE_OPERAND (scalar, 0);
3094 }
3095
3096 if (!VAR_P (scalar)
3097 || !is_global_var (scalar)
3098 || !TREE_READONLY (scalar)
3099 || !DECL_INITIAL (scalar)
3100 || TREE_CODE (DECL_INITIAL (scalar)) != CONSTRUCTOR)
3101 return NULL;
3102
3103 return find_constructor_constant_at_offset (DECL_INITIAL (scalar), offset);
3104}

3106/* Retrieve value from aggregate jump function AGG or static initializer of
3107 SCALAR (which can be NULL) for the given OFFSET or return NULL if there is
3108 none. BY_REF specifies whether the value has to be passed by reference or
3109 by value. If FROM_GLOBAL_CONSTANT is non-NULL, then the boolean it points
3110 to is set to true if the value comes from an initializer of a constant. */
3111
3112tree
3113ipa_find_agg_cst_for_param (struct ipa_agg_jump_function *agg, tree scalar,
3114 HOST_WIDE_INT offset, bool by_ref,
3115 bool *from_global_constant)
3116{
3117 struct ipa_agg_jf_item *item;
3118 int i;
3119
3120 if (scalar)
3121 {
3122 tree res = ipa_find_agg_cst_from_init (scalar, offset, by_ref);
3123 if (res)
3124 {
3125 if (from_global_constant)
3126 *from_global_constant = true;
3127 return res;
3128 }
3129 }
3130
3131 if (!agg
3132 || by_ref != agg->by_ref)
3133 return NULL;
3134
3135 FOR_EACH_VEC_SAFE_ELT (agg->items, i, item)
3136 if (item->offset == offset)
3137 {
3138 /* Currently we do not have clobber values, return NULL for them once
3139 we do. */
3140 gcc_checking_assert (is_gimple_ip_invariant (item->value));
3141 if (from_global_constant)
3142 *from_global_constant = false;
3143 return item->value;
3144 }
3145 return NULL;
3146}

3205/* If JFUNC is a constant jump function with a usable rdesc, decrement its
3206 refcount and if it hits zero, remove reference to SYMBOL from the caller of
3207 the edge specified in the rdesc. Return false if either the symbol or the
3208 reference could not be found, otherwise return true. */
3209
3210static bool
3211try_decrement_rdesc_refcount (struct ipa_jump_func *jfunc)
3212{
3213 struct ipa_cst_ref_desc *rdesc;
3214 if (jfunc->type == IPA_JF_CONST
3215 && (rdesc = jfunc_rdesc_usable (jfunc))
3216 && --rdesc->refcount == 0)
3217 {
3218 symtab_node *symbol = cgraph_node_for_jfunc (jfunc);
3219 if (!symbol)
3220 return false;
3221
3222 return remove_described_reference (symbol, rdesc);
3223 }

3227/* Try to find a destination for indirect edge IE that corresponds to a simple
3228 call or a call of a member function pointer and where the destination is a
3229 pointer formal parameter described by jump function JFUNC. If it can be
3230 determined, return the newly direct edge, otherwise return NULL.
3231 NEW_ROOT_INFO is the node info that JFUNC lattices are relative to. */
3232
3233static struct cgraph_edge *
3234try_make_edge_direct_simple_call (struct cgraph_edge *ie,
3235 struct ipa_jump_func *jfunc,
3236 struct ipa_node_params *new_root_info)
3237{
3238 struct cgraph_edge *cs;
3239 tree target;
3240 bool agg_contents = ie->indirect_info->agg_contents;
3241 tree scalar = ipa_value_from_jfunc (new_root_info, jfunc);
3242 if (agg_contents)
3243 {
3244 bool from_global_constant;
3245 target = ipa_find_agg_cst_for_param (&jfunc->agg, scalar,
3246 ie->indirect_info->offset,
3247 ie->indirect_info->by_ref,
3248 &from_global_constant);
3249 if (target
3250 && !from_global_constant
3251 && !ie->indirect_info->guaranteed_unmodified)
3252 return NULL;
3253 }
3254 else
3255 target = scalar;
3256 if (!target)
3257 return NULL;
3258 cs = ipa_make_edge_direct_to_target (ie, target);
3259
3260 if (cs && !agg_contents)
3261 {
3262 bool ok;
3263 gcc_checking_assert (cs->callee
3264 && (cs != ie
3265 || jfunc->type != IPA_JF_CONST
3266 || !cgraph_node_for_jfunc (jfunc)
3267 || cs->callee == cgraph_node_for_jfunc (jfunc)));
3268 ok = try_decrement_rdesc_refcount (jfunc);
3269 gcc_checking_assert (ok);
3270 }
3271
3272 return cs;
3273}

3275/* Return the target to be used in cases of impossible devirtualization. IE
3276 and target (the latter can be NULL) are dumped when dumping is enabled. */
3277
3278tree
3279ipa_impossible_devirt_target (struct cgraph_edge *ie, tree target)
3280{
3281 if (dump_file)
3282 {
3283 if (target)
3284 fprintf (dump_file,
3285 "Type inconsistent devirtualization: %s/%i->%s\n",
3286 ie->caller->name (), ie->caller->order,
3287 IDENTIFIER_POINTER (DECL_ASSEMBLER_NAME (target)));
3288 else
3289 fprintf (dump_file,
3290 "No devirtualization target in %s/%i\n",
3291 ie->caller->name (), ie->caller->order);
3292 }
3293 tree new_target = builtin_decl_implicit (BUILT_IN_UNREACHABLE);
3294 cgraph_node::get_create (new_target);
3295 return new_target;
3296}

3298/* Try to find a destination for indirect edge IE that corresponds to a virtual
3299 call based on a formal parameter which is described by jump function JFUNC
3300 and if it can be determined, make it direct and return the direct edge.
3301 Otherwise, return NULL. CTX describes the polymorphic context that the
3302 parameter the call is based on brings along with it. */
3303
3304static struct cgraph_edge *
3305try_make_edge_direct_virtual_call (struct cgraph_edge *ie,
3306 struct ipa_jump_func *jfunc,
3307 struct ipa_polymorphic_call_context ctx)
3308{
3309 tree target = NULL;
3310 bool speculative = false;
3311
3312 if (!opt_for_fn (ie->caller->decl, flag_devirtualize))
3313 return NULL;
3314
3315 gcc_assert (!ie->indirect_info->by_ref);
3316
3317 /* Try to do lookup via known virtual table pointer value. */
3318 if (!ie->indirect_info->vptr_changed
3319 || opt_for_fn (ie->caller->decl, flag_devirtualize_speculatively))
3320 {
3321 tree vtable;
3322 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT offset;
3323 tree scalar = (jfunc->type == IPA_JF_CONST) ? ipa_get_jf_constant (jfunc)
3324 : NULL;
3325 tree t = ipa_find_agg_cst_for_param (&jfunc->agg, scalar,
3326 ie->indirect_info->offset,
3327 true);
3328 if (t && vtable_pointer_value_to_vtable (t, &vtable, &offset))
3329 {
3330 bool can_refer;
3331 t = gimple_get_virt_method_for_vtable (ie->indirect_info->otr_token,
3332 vtable, offset, &can_refer);
3333 if (can_refer)
3334 {
3335 if (!t
3336 || (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (t)) == FUNCTION_TYPE
3337 && DECL_FUNCTION_CODE (t) == BUILT_IN_UNREACHABLE)
3338 || !possible_polymorphic_call_target_p
3339 (ie, cgraph_node::get (t)))
3340 {
3341 /* Do not speculate builtin_unreachable, it is stupid! */
3342 if (!ie->indirect_info->vptr_changed)
3343 target = ipa_impossible_devirt_target (ie, target);
3344 else
3345 target = NULL;
3346 }
3347 else
3348 {
3349 target = t;
3350 speculative = ie->indirect_info->vptr_changed;
3351 }
3352 }
3353 }
3354 }
3355
3356 ipa_polymorphic_call_context ie_context (ie);
3357 vec <cgraph_node *>targets;
3358 bool final;
3359
3360 ctx.offset_by (ie->indirect_info->offset);
3361 if (ie->indirect_info->vptr_changed)
3362 ctx.possible_dynamic_type_change (ie->in_polymorphic_cdtor,
3363 ie->indirect_info->otr_type);
3364 ctx.combine_with (ie_context, ie->indirect_info->otr_type);
3365 targets = possible_polymorphic_call_targets
3366 (ie->indirect_info->otr_type,
3367 ie->indirect_info->otr_token,
3368 ctx, &final);
3369 if (final && targets.length () <= 1)
3370 {
3371 speculative = false;
3372 if (targets.length () == 1)
3373 target = targets[0]->decl;
3374 else
3375 target = ipa_impossible_devirt_target (ie, NULL_TREE);
3376 }
3377 else if (!target && opt_for_fn (ie->caller->decl, flag_devirtualize_speculatively)
3378 && !ie->speculative && ie->maybe_hot_p ())
3379 {
3380 cgraph_node *n;
3381 n = try_speculative_devirtualization (ie->indirect_info->otr_type,
3382 ie->indirect_info->otr_token,
3383 ie->indirect_info->context);
3384 if (n)
3385 {
3386 target = n->decl;
3387 speculative = true;
3388 }
3389 }
3390
3391 if (target)
3392 {
3393 if (!possible_polymorphic_call_target_p
3394 (ie, cgraph_node::get_create (target)))
3395 {
3396 if (speculative)
3397 return NULL;
3398 target = ipa_impossible_devirt_target (ie, target);
3399 }
3400 return ipa_make_edge_direct_to_target (ie, target, speculative);
3401 }
3402 else
3403 return NULL;
3404}

3406/* Update the param called notes associated with NODE when CS is being inlined,
3407 assuming NODE is (potentially indirectly) inlined into CS->callee.
3408 Moreover, if the callee is discovered to be constant, create a new cgraph
3409 edge for it. Newly discovered indirect edges will be added to *NEW_EDGES,
3410 unless NEW_EDGES is NULL. Return true iff a new edge(s) were created. */
3411
3412static bool
3413update_indirect_edges_after_inlining (struct cgraph_edge *cs,
3414 struct cgraph_node *node,
3415 vec<cgraph_edge *> *new_edges)
3416{
3417 struct ipa_edge_args *top;
3418 struct cgraph_edge *ie, *next_ie, *new_direct_edge;
3419 struct ipa_node_params *new_root_info;
3420 bool res = false;
3421
3422 ipa_check_create_edge_args ();
3423 top = IPA_EDGE_REF (cs);
3424 new_root_info = IPA_NODE_REF (cs->caller->global.inlined_to
3425 ? cs->caller->global.inlined_to
3426 : cs->caller);
3427
3428 for (ie = node->indirect_calls; ie; ie = next_ie)
3429 {
3430 struct cgraph_indirect_call_info *ici = ie->indirect_info;
3431 struct ipa_jump_func *jfunc;
3432 int param_index;
3433 cgraph_node *spec_target = NULL;
3434
3435 next_ie = ie->next_callee;
3436
3437 if (ici->param_index == -1)
3438 continue;
3439
3440 /* We must check range due to calls with variable number of arguments: */
3441 if (ici->param_index >= ipa_get_cs_argument_count (top))
3442 {
3443 ici->param_index = -1;
3444 continue;
3445 }
3446
3447 param_index = ici->param_index;
3448 jfunc = ipa_get_ith_jump_func (top, param_index);
3449
3450 if (ie->speculative)
3451 {
3452 struct cgraph_edge *de;
3453 struct ipa_ref *ref;
3454 ie->speculative_call_info (de, ie, ref);
3455 spec_target = de->callee;
3456 }
3457
3458 if (!opt_for_fn (node->decl, flag_indirect_inlining))
3459 new_direct_edge = NULL;
3460 else if (ici->polymorphic)
3461 {
3462 ipa_polymorphic_call_context ctx;
3463 ctx = ipa_context_from_jfunc (new_root_info, cs, param_index, jfunc);
3464 new_direct_edge = try_make_edge_direct_virtual_call (ie, jfunc, ctx);
3465 }
3466 else
3467 new_direct_edge = try_make_edge_direct_simple_call (ie, jfunc,
3468 new_root_info);
3469 /* If speculation was removed, then we need to do nothing. */
3470 if (new_direct_edge && new_direct_edge != ie
3471 && new_direct_edge->callee == spec_target)
3472 {
3473 new_direct_edge->indirect_inlining_edge = 1;
3474 top = IPA_EDGE_REF (cs);
3475 res = true;
3476 if (!new_direct_edge->speculative)
3477 continue;
3478 }
3479 else if (new_direct_edge)
3480 {
3481 new_direct_edge->indirect_inlining_edge = 1;
3482 if (new_direct_edge->call_stmt)
3483 new_direct_edge->call_stmt_cannot_inline_p
3484 = !gimple_check_call_matching_types (
3485 new_direct_edge->call_stmt,
3486 new_direct_edge->callee->decl, false);
3487 if (new_edges)
3488 {
3489 new_edges->safe_push (new_direct_edge);
3490 res = true;
3491 }
3492 top = IPA_EDGE_REF (cs);
3493 /* If speculative edge was introduced we still need to update
3494 call info of the indirect edge. */
3495 if (!new_direct_edge->speculative)
3496 continue;
3497 }
3498 if (jfunc->type == IPA_JF_PASS_THROUGH
3499 && ipa_get_jf_pass_through_operation (jfunc) == NOP_EXPR)
3500 {
3501 if (ici->agg_contents
3502 && !ipa_get_jf_pass_through_agg_preserved (jfunc)
3503 && !ici->polymorphic)
3504 ici->param_index = -1;
3505 else
3506 {
3507 ici->param_index = ipa_get_jf_pass_through_formal_id (jfunc);
3508 if (ici->polymorphic
3509 && !ipa_get_jf_pass_through_type_preserved (jfunc))
3510 ici->vptr_changed = true;
3511 }
3512 }
3513 else if (jfunc->type == IPA_JF_ANCESTOR)
3514 {
3515 if (ici->agg_contents
3516 && !ipa_get_jf_ancestor_agg_preserved (jfunc)
3517 && !ici->polymorphic)
3518 ici->param_index = -1;
3519 else
3520 {
3521 ici->param_index = ipa_get_jf_ancestor_formal_id (jfunc);
3522 ici->offset += ipa_get_jf_ancestor_offset (jfunc);
3523 if (ici->polymorphic
3524 && !ipa_get_jf_ancestor_type_preserved (jfunc))
3525 ici->vptr_changed = true;
3526 }
3527 }
3528 else
3529 /* Either we can find a destination for this edge now or never. */
3530 ici->param_index = -1;
3531 }
3532
3533 return res;
3534}
3535
3536/* Recursively traverse subtree of NODE (including node) made of inlined
3537 cgraph_edges when CS has been inlined and invoke
3538 update_indirect_edges_after_inlining on all nodes and
3539 update_jump_functions_after_inlining on all non-inlined edges that lead out
3540 of this subtree. Newly discovered indirect edges will be added to
3541 *NEW_EDGES, unless NEW_EDGES is NULL. Return true iff a new edge(s) were
3542 created. */
3543
3544static bool
3545propagate_info_to_inlined_callees (struct cgraph_edge *cs,
3546 struct cgraph_node *node,
3547 vec<cgraph_edge *> *new_edges)
3548{
3549 struct cgraph_edge *e;
3550 bool res;
3551
3552 res = update_indirect_edges_after_inlining (cs, node, new_edges);
3553
3554 for (e = node->callees; e; e = e->next_callee)
3555 if (!e->inline_failed)
3556 res |= propagate_info_to_inlined_callees (cs, e->callee, new_edges);
3557 else
3558 update_jump_functions_after_inlining (cs, e);
3559 for (e = node->indirect_calls; e; e = e->next_callee)
3560 update_jump_functions_after_inlining (cs, e);
3561
3562 return res;
3563}
3564
3565/* Combine two controlled uses counts as done during inlining. */
3566
3567static int
3568combine_controlled_uses_counters (int c, int d)
3569{
3570 if (c == IPA_UNDESCRIBED_USE || d == IPA_UNDESCRIBED_USE)
3571 return IPA_UNDESCRIBED_USE;
3572 else
3573 return c + d - 1;
3574}
3575
3576/* Propagate number of controlled users from CS->caleee to the new root of the
3577 tree of inlined nodes. */
3578
3579static void
3580propagate_controlled_uses (struct cgraph_edge *cs)
3581{
3582 struct ipa_edge_args *args = IPA_EDGE_REF (cs);
3583 struct cgraph_node *new_root = cs->caller->global.inlined_to
3584 ? cs->caller->global.inlined_to : cs->caller;
3585 struct ipa_node_params *new_root_info = IPA_NODE_REF (new_root);
3586 struct ipa_node_params *old_root_info = IPA_NODE_REF (cs->callee);
3587 int count, i;
3588
3589 count = MIN (ipa_get_cs_argument_count (args),
3590 ipa_get_param_count (old_root_info));
3591 for (i = 0; i < count; i++)
3592 {
3593 struct ipa_jump_func *jf = ipa_get_ith_jump_func (args, i);
3594 struct ipa_cst_ref_desc *rdesc;
3595
3596 if (jf->type == IPA_JF_PASS_THROUGH)
3597 {
3598 int src_idx, c, d;
3599 src_idx = ipa_get_jf_pass_through_formal_id (jf);
3600 c = ipa_get_controlled_uses (new_root_info, src_idx);
3601 d = ipa_get_controlled_uses (old_root_info, i);
3602
3603 gcc_checking_assert (ipa_get_jf_pass_through_operation (jf)
3604 == NOP_EXPR || c == IPA_UNDESCRIBED_USE);
3605 c = combine_controlled_uses_counters (c, d);
3606 ipa_set_controlled_uses (new_root_info, src_idx, c);
3607 if (c == 0 && new_root_info->ipcp_orig_node)
3608 {
3609 struct cgraph_node *n;
3610 struct ipa_ref *ref;
3611 tree t = new_root_info->known_csts[src_idx];
3612
3613 if (t && TREE_CODE (t) == ADDR_EXPR
3614 && TREE_CODE (TREE_OPERAND (t, 0)) == FUNCTION_DECL
3615 && (n = cgraph_node::get (TREE_OPERAND (t, 0)))
3616 && (ref = new_root->find_reference (n, NULL, 0)))
3617 {
3618 if (dump_file)
3619 fprintf (dump_file, "ipa-prop: Removing cloning-created "
3620 "reference from %s/%i to %s/%i.\n",
3621 xstrdup_for_dump (new_root->name ()),
3622 new_root->order,
3623 xstrdup_for_dump (n->name ()), n->order);
3624 ref->remove_reference ();
3625 }
3626 }
3627 }
3628 else if (jf->type == IPA_JF_CONST
3629 && (rdesc = jfunc_rdesc_usable (jf)))
3630 {
3631 int d = ipa_get_controlled_uses (old_root_info, i);
3632 int c = rdesc->refcount;
3633 rdesc->refcount = combine_controlled_uses_counters (c, d);
3634 if (rdesc->refcount == 0)
3635 {
3636 tree cst = ipa_get_jf_constant (jf);
3637 struct cgraph_node *n;
3638 gcc_checking_assert (TREE_CODE (cst) == ADDR_EXPR
3639 && TREE_CODE (TREE_OPERAND (cst, 0))
3640 == FUNCTION_DECL);
3641 n = cgraph_node::get (TREE_OPERAND (cst, 0));
3642 if (n)
3643 {
3644 struct cgraph_node *clone;
3645 bool ok;
3646 ok = remove_described_reference (n, rdesc);
3647 gcc_checking_assert (ok);
3648
3649 clone = cs->caller;
3650 while (clone->global.inlined_to
3651 && clone != rdesc->cs->caller
3652 && IPA_NODE_REF (clone)->ipcp_orig_node)
3653 {
3654 struct ipa_ref *ref;
3655 ref = clone->find_reference (n, NULL, 0);
3656 if (ref)
3657 {
3658 if (dump_file)
3659 fprintf (dump_file, "ipa-prop: Removing "
3660 "cloning-created reference "
3661 "from %s/%i to %s/%i.\n",
3662 xstrdup_for_dump (clone->name ()),
3663 clone->order,
3664 xstrdup_for_dump (n->name ()),
3665 n->order);
3666 ref->remove_reference ();
3667 }
3668 clone = clone->callers->caller;
3669 }
3670 }
3671 }
3672 }
3673 }
3674
3675 for (i = ipa_get_param_count (old_root_info);
3676 i < ipa_get_cs_argument_count (args);
3677 i++)
3678 {
3679 struct ipa_jump_func *jf = ipa_get_ith_jump_func (args, i);
3680
3681 if (jf->type == IPA_JF_CONST)
3682 {
3683 struct ipa_cst_ref_desc *rdesc = jfunc_rdesc_usable (jf);
3684 if (rdesc)
3685 rdesc->refcount = IPA_UNDESCRIBED_USE;
3686 }
3687 else if (jf->type == IPA_JF_PASS_THROUGH)
3688 ipa_set_controlled_uses (new_root_info,
3689 jf->value.pass_through.formal_id,
3690 IPA_UNDESCRIBED_USE);
3691 }
3692}

3694/* Update jump functions and call note functions on inlining the call site CS.
3695 CS is expected to lead to a node already cloned by
3696 cgraph_clone_inline_nodes. Newly discovered indirect edges will be added to
3697 *NEW_EDGES, unless NEW_EDGES is NULL. Return true iff a new edge(s) were +
3698 created. */
3699
3700bool
3701ipa_propagate_indirect_call_infos (struct cgraph_edge *cs,
3702 vec<cgraph_edge *> *new_edges)
3703{
3704 bool changed;
3705 /* Do nothing if the preparation phase has not been carried out yet
3706 (i.e. during early inlining). */
3707 if (!ipa_node_params_sum)
3708 return false;
3709 gcc_assert (ipa_edge_args_vector);
3710
3711 propagate_controlled_uses (cs);
3712 changed = propagate_info_to_inlined_callees (cs, cs->callee, new_edges);
3713
3714 return changed;
3715}

3717/* Ensure that array of edge arguments infos is big enough to accommodate a
3718 structure for all edges and reallocates it if not. Also, allocate
3719 associated hash tables is they do not already exist. */

3722ipa_check_create_edge_args (void)
3723{

3725 <= (unsigned) symtab->edges_max_uid)
3726 vec_safe_grow_cleared (ipa_edge_args_vector, symtab->edges_max_uid + 1);
3727 if (!ipa_bits_hash_table)
3728 ipa_bits_hash_table = hash_table<ipa_bit_ggc_hash_traits>::create_ggc (37);
3729 if (!ipa_vr_hash_table)
3730 ipa_vr_hash_table = hash_table<ipa_vr_ggc_hash_traits>::create_ggc (37);
3731}

3794/* Hook that is called by cgraph.c when an edge is removed. */
3795
3796static void
3797ipa_edge_removal_hook (struct cgraph_edge *cs, void *data ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED)
3798{
3799 struct ipa_edge_args *args;
3800
3801 /* During IPA-CP updating we can be called on not-yet analyzed clones. */
3802 if (vec_safe_length (ipa_edge_args_vector) <= (unsigned)cs->uid)
3803 return;
3804
3805 args = IPA_EDGE_REF (cs);
3806 if (args->jump_functions)
3807 {
3808 struct ipa_jump_func *jf;
3809 int i;
3810 FOR_EACH_VEC_ELT (*args->jump_functions, i, jf)
3811 {
3812 struct ipa_cst_ref_desc *rdesc;
3813 try_decrement_rdesc_refcount (jf);
3814 if (jf->type == IPA_JF_CONST
3815 && (rdesc = ipa_get_jf_constant_rdesc (jf))
3816 && rdesc->cs == cs)
3817 rdesc->cs = NULL;
3818 }
3819 }
3820
3821 ipa_free_edge_args_substructures (IPA_EDGE_REF (cs));
3822}
3823
3824/* Hook that is called by cgraph.c when an edge is duplicated. */
3825
3826static void
3827ipa_edge_duplication_hook (struct cgraph_edge *src, struct cgraph_edge *dst,
3828 void *)
3829{
3830 struct ipa_edge_args *old_args, *new_args;
3831 unsigned int i;
3832
3833 ipa_check_create_edge_args ();
3834
3835 old_args = IPA_EDGE_REF (src);
3836 new_args = IPA_EDGE_REF (dst);
3837
3838 new_args->jump_functions = vec_safe_copy (old_args->jump_functions);
3839 if (old_args->polymorphic_call_contexts)
3840 new_args->polymorphic_call_contexts
3841 = vec_safe_copy (old_args->polymorphic_call_contexts);
3842
3843 for (i = 0; i < vec_safe_length (old_args->jump_functions); i++)
3844 {
3845 struct ipa_jump_func *src_jf = ipa_get_ith_jump_func (old_args, i);
3846 struct ipa_jump_func *dst_jf = ipa_get_ith_jump_func (new_args, i);
3847
3848 dst_jf->agg.items = vec_safe_copy (dst_jf->agg.items);
3849
3850 if (src_jf->type == IPA_JF_CONST)
3851 {
3852 struct ipa_cst_ref_desc *src_rdesc = jfunc_rdesc_usable (src_jf);
3853
3854 if (!src_rdesc)
3855 dst_jf->value.constant.rdesc = NULL;
3856 else if (src->caller == dst->caller)
3857 {
3858 struct ipa_ref *ref;
3859 symtab_node *n = cgraph_node_for_jfunc (src_jf);
3860 gcc_checking_assert (n);
3861 ref = src->caller->find_reference (n, src->call_stmt,
3862 src->lto_stmt_uid);
3863 gcc_checking_assert (ref);
3864 dst->caller->clone_reference (ref, ref->stmt);
3865
3866 struct ipa_cst_ref_desc *dst_rdesc = ipa_refdesc_pool.allocate ();
3867 dst_rdesc->cs = dst;
3868 dst_rdesc->refcount = src_rdesc->refcount;
3869 dst_rdesc->next_duplicate = NULL;
3870 dst_jf->value.constant.rdesc = dst_rdesc;
3871 }
3872 else if (src_rdesc->cs == src)
3873 {
3874 struct ipa_cst_ref_desc *dst_rdesc = ipa_refdesc_pool.allocate ();
3875 dst_rdesc->cs = dst;
3876 dst_rdesc->refcount = src_rdesc->refcount;
3877 dst_rdesc->next_duplicate = src_rdesc->next_duplicate;
3878 src_rdesc->next_duplicate = dst_rdesc;
3879 dst_jf->value.constant.rdesc = dst_rdesc;
3880 }
3881 else
3882 {
3883 struct ipa_cst_ref_desc *dst_rdesc;
3884 /* This can happen during inlining, when a JFUNC can refer to a
3885 reference taken in a function up in the tree of inline clones.
3886 We need to find the duplicate that refers to our tree of
3887 inline clones. */
3888
3889 gcc_assert (dst->caller->global.inlined_to);
3890 for (dst_rdesc = src_rdesc->next_duplicate;
3891 dst_rdesc;
3892 dst_rdesc = dst_rdesc->next_duplicate)
3893 {
3894 struct cgraph_node *top;
3895 top = dst_rdesc->cs->caller->global.inlined_to
3896 ? dst_rdesc->cs->caller->global.inlined_to
3897 : dst_rdesc->cs->caller;
3898 if (dst->caller->global.inlined_to == top)
3899 break;
3900 }
3901 gcc_assert (dst_rdesc);
3902 dst_jf->value.constant.rdesc = dst_rdesc;
3903 }
3904 }
3905 else if (dst_jf->type == IPA_JF_PASS_THROUGH
3906 && src->caller == dst->caller)
3907 {
3908 struct cgraph_node *inline_root = dst->caller->global.inlined_to
3909 ? dst->caller->global.inlined_to : dst->caller;
3910 struct ipa_node_params *root_info = IPA_NODE_REF (inline_root);
3911 int idx = ipa_get_jf_pass_through_formal_id (dst_jf);
3912
3913 int c = ipa_get_controlled_uses (root_info, idx);
3914 if (c != IPA_UNDESCRIBED_USE)
3915 {
3916 c++;
3917 ipa_set_controlled_uses (root_info, idx, c);
3918 }
3919 }
3920 }
3921}

3932/* Hook that is called by summary when a node is duplicated. */
3933
3934void
3935ipa_node_params_t::duplicate(cgraph_node *src, cgraph_node *dst,
3936 ipa_node_params *old_info,
3937 ipa_node_params *new_info)
3938{
3939 ipa_agg_replacement_value *old_av, *new_av;
3940
3941 new_info->descriptors = vec_safe_copy (old_info->descriptors);
3942 new_info->lattices = NULL;
3943 new_info->ipcp_orig_node = old_info->ipcp_orig_node;
3944 new_info->known_csts = old_info->known_csts.copy ();
3945 new_info->known_contexts = old_info->known_contexts.copy ();
3946
3947 new_info->analysis_done = old_info->analysis_done;
3948 new_info->node_enqueued = old_info->node_enqueued;
3949 new_info->versionable = old_info->versionable;
3950
3951 old_av = ipa_get_agg_replacements_for_node (src);
3952 if (old_av)
3953 {
3954 new_av = NULL;
3955 while (old_av)
3956 {
3957 struct ipa_agg_replacement_value *v;
3958
3959 v = ggc_alloc<ipa_agg_replacement_value> ();
3960 memcpy (v, old_av, sizeof (*v));
3961 v->next = new_av;
3962 new_av = v;
3963 old_av = old_av->next;
3964 }
3965 ipa_set_node_agg_value_chain (dst, new_av);
3966 }
3967
3968 ipcp_transformation_summary *src_trans
3969 = ipcp_get_transformation_summary (src);
3970
3971 if (src_trans)
3972 {
3973 ipcp_grow_transformations_if_necessary ();
3974 src_trans = ipcp_get_transformation_summary (src);
3975 ipcp_transformation_summary *dst_trans
3976 = ipcp_get_transformation_summary (dst);
3977
3978 dst_trans->bits = vec_safe_copy (src_trans->bits);
3979
3980 const vec<ipa_vr, va_gc> *src_vr = src_trans->m_vr;
3981 vec<ipa_vr, va_gc> *&dst_vr
3982 = ipcp_get_transformation_summary (dst)->m_vr;
3983 if (vec_safe_length (src_trans->m_vr) > 0)
3984 {
3985 vec_safe_reserve_exact (dst_vr, src_vr->length ());
3986 for (unsigned i = 0; i < src_vr->length (); ++i)
3987 dst_vr->quick_push ((*src_vr)[i]);
3988 }
3989 }
3990}

4102/* Return a heap allocated vector containing formal parameters of FNDECL. */
4103
4104vec<tree>
4105ipa_get_vector_of_formal_parms (tree fndecl)
4106{
4107 vec<tree> args;

4109 tree parm;
4110
4111 gcc_assert (!flag_wpa);
4112 count = count_formal_params (fndecl);
4113 args.create (count);

4120/* Return a heap allocated vector containing types of formal parameters of
4121 function type FNTYPE. */

4125{
4126 vec<tree> types;

4135 types.quick_push (TREE_VALUE (t));

4140/* Modify the function declaration FNDECL and its type according to the plan in
4141 ADJUSTMENTS. It also sets base fields of individual adjustments structures
4142 to reflect the actual parameters being modified which are determined by the
4143 base_index field. */
4144
4145void
4146ipa_modify_formal_parameters (tree fndecl, ipa_parm_adjustment_vec adjustments)
4147{
4148 vec<tree> oparms = ipa_get_vector_of_formal_parms (fndecl);
4149 tree orig_type = TREE_TYPE (fndecl);
4150 tree old_arg_types = TYPE_ARG_TYPES (orig_type);
4151
4152 /* The following test is an ugly hack, some functions simply don't have any
4153 arguments in their type. This is probably a bug but well... */
4154 bool care_for_types = (old_arg_types != NULL_TREE);
4155 bool last_parm_void;
4156 vec<tree> otypes;
4157 if (care_for_types)
4158 {
4159 last_parm_void = (TREE_VALUE (tree_last (old_arg_types))
4160 == void_type_node);
4161 otypes = ipa_get_vector_of_formal_parm_types (orig_type);
4162 if (last_parm_void)
4163 gcc_assert (oparms.length () + 1 == otypes.length ());
4164 else
4165 gcc_assert (oparms.length () == otypes.length ());
4166 }
4167 else
4168 {
4169 last_parm_void = false;
4170 otypes.create (0);
4171 }
4172
4173 int len = adjustments.length ();
4174 tree *link = &DECL_ARGUMENTS (fndecl);
4175 tree new_arg_types = NULL;
4176 for (int i = 0; i < len; i++)
4177 {
4178 struct ipa_parm_adjustment *adj;
4179 gcc_assert (link);
4180
4181 adj = &adjustments[i];
4182 tree parm;
4183 if (adj->op == IPA_PARM_OP_NEW)
4184 parm = NULL;
4185 else
4186 parm = oparms[adj->base_index];
4187 adj->base = parm;
4188
4189 if (adj->op == IPA_PARM_OP_COPY)
4190 {
4191 if (care_for_types)
4192 new_arg_types = tree_cons (NULL_TREE, otypes[adj->base_index],
4193 new_arg_types);
4194 *link = parm;
4195 link = &DECL_CHAIN (parm);
4196 }
4197 else if (adj->op != IPA_PARM_OP_REMOVE)
4198 {
4199 tree new_parm;
4200 tree ptype;
4201
4202 if (adj->by_ref)
4203 ptype = build_pointer_type (adj->type);
4204 else
4205 {
4206 ptype = adj->type;
4207 if (is_gimple_reg_type (ptype)
4208 && TYPE_MODE (ptype) != BLKmode)
4209 {
4210 unsigned malign = GET_MODE_ALIGNMENT (TYPE_MODE (ptype));
4211 if (TYPE_ALIGN (ptype) != malign)
4212 ptype = build_aligned_type (ptype, malign);
4213 }
4214 }
4215
4216 if (care_for_types)
4217 new_arg_types = tree_cons (NULL_TREE, ptype, new_arg_types);
4218
4219 new_parm = build_decl (UNKNOWN_LOCATION, PARM_DECL, NULL_TREE,
4220 ptype);
4221 const char *prefix = adj->arg_prefix ? adj->arg_prefix : "SYNTH";
4222 DECL_NAME (new_parm) = create_tmp_var_name (prefix);
4223 DECL_ARTIFICIAL (new_parm) = 1;
4224 DECL_ARG_TYPE (new_parm) = ptype;
4225 DECL_CONTEXT (new_parm) = fndecl;
4226 TREE_USED (new_parm) = 1;
4227 DECL_IGNORED_P (new_parm) = 1;
4228 layout_decl (new_parm, 0);
4229
4230 if (adj->op == IPA_PARM_OP_NEW)
4231 adj->base = NULL;
4232 else
4233 adj->base = parm;
4234 adj->new_decl = new_parm;
4235
4236 *link = new_parm;
4237 link = &DECL_CHAIN (new_parm);
4238 }
4239 }
4240
4241 *link = NULL_TREE;
4242
4243 tree new_reversed = NULL;
4244 if (care_for_types)
4245 {
4246 new_reversed = nreverse (new_arg_types);
4247 if (last_parm_void)
4248 {
4249 if (new_reversed)
4250 TREE_CHAIN (new_arg_types) = void_list_node;
4251 else
4252 new_reversed = void_list_node;
4253 }
4254 }
4255
4256 /* Use copy_node to preserve as much as possible from original type
4257 (debug info, attribute lists etc.)
4258 Exception is METHOD_TYPEs must have THIS argument.
4259 When we are asked to remove it, we need to build new FUNCTION_TYPE
4260 instead. */
4261 tree new_type = NULL;
4262 if (TREE_CODE (orig_type) != METHOD_TYPE
4263 || (adjustments[0].op == IPA_PARM_OP_COPY
4264 && adjustments[0].base_index == 0))
4265 {
4266 new_type = build_distinct_type_copy (orig_type);
4267 TYPE_ARG_TYPES (new_type) = new_reversed;
4268 }
4269 else
4270 {
4271 new_type
4272 = build_distinct_type_copy (build_function_type (TREE_TYPE (orig_type),
4273 new_reversed));
4274 TYPE_CONTEXT (new_type) = TYPE_CONTEXT (orig_type);
4275 DECL_VINDEX (fndecl) = NULL_TREE;
4276 }
4277
4278 /* When signature changes, we need to clear builtin info. */
4279 if (DECL_BUILT_IN (fndecl))
4280 {
4281 DECL_BUILT_IN_CLASS (fndecl) = NOT_BUILT_IN;
4282 DECL_FUNCTION_CODE (fndecl) = (enum built_in_function) 0;
4283 }
4284
4285 TREE_TYPE (fndecl) = new_type;
4286 DECL_VIRTUAL_P (fndecl) = 0;
4287 DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (fndecl) = NULL;
4288 otypes.release ();
4289 oparms.release ();
4290}
4291
4292/* Modify actual arguments of a function call CS as indicated in ADJUSTMENTS.
4293 If this is a directly recursive call, CS must be NULL. Otherwise it must
4294 contain the corresponding call graph edge. */
4295
4296void
4297ipa_modify_call_arguments (struct cgraph_edge *cs, gcall *stmt,
4298 ipa_parm_adjustment_vec adjustments)
4299{
4300 struct cgraph_node *current_node = cgraph_node::get (current_function_decl);
4301 vec<tree> vargs;
4302 vec<tree, va_gc> **debug_args = NULL;
4303 gcall *new_stmt;
4304 gimple_stmt_iterator gsi, prev_gsi;
4305 tree callee_decl;
4306 int i, len;
4307
4308 len = adjustments.length ();
4309 vargs.create (len);
4310 callee_decl = !cs ? gimple_call_fndecl (stmt) : cs->callee->decl;
4311 current_node->remove_stmt_references (stmt);
4312
4313 gsi = gsi_for_stmt (stmt);
4314 prev_gsi = gsi;
4315 gsi_prev (&prev_gsi);
4316 for (i = 0; i < len; i++)
4317 {
4318 struct ipa_parm_adjustment *adj;
4319
4320 adj = &adjustments[i];
4321
4322 if (adj->op == IPA_PARM_OP_COPY)
4323 {
4324 tree arg = gimple_call_arg (stmt, adj->base_index);
4325
4326 vargs.quick_push (arg);
4327 }
4328 else if (adj->op != IPA_PARM_OP_REMOVE)
4329 {
4330 tree expr, base, off;
4331 location_t loc;
4332 unsigned int deref_align = 0;
4333 bool deref_base = false;
4334
4335 /* We create a new parameter out of the value of the old one, we can
4336 do the following kind of transformations:
4337
4338 - A scalar passed by reference is converted to a scalar passed by
4339 value. (adj->by_ref is false and the type of the original
4340 actual argument is a pointer to a scalar).
4341
4342 - A part of an aggregate is passed instead of the whole aggregate.
4343 The part can be passed either by value or by reference, this is
4344 determined by value of adj->by_ref. Moreover, the code below
4345 handles both situations when the original aggregate is passed by
4346 value (its type is not a pointer) and when it is passed by
4347 reference (it is a pointer to an aggregate).
4348
4349 When the new argument is passed by reference (adj->by_ref is true)
4350 it must be a part of an aggregate and therefore we form it by
4351 simply taking the address of a reference inside the original
4352 aggregate. */
4353
4354 gcc_checking_assert (adj->offset % BITS_PER_UNIT == 0);
4355 base = gimple_call_arg (stmt, adj->base_index);
4356 loc = gimple_location (stmt);
4357
4358 if (TREE_CODE (base) != ADDR_EXPR
4359 && POINTER_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (base)))
4360 off = build_int_cst (adj->alias_ptr_type,
4361 adj->offset / BITS_PER_UNIT);
4362 else
4363 {
4364 HOST_WIDE_INT base_offset;
4365 tree prev_base;
4366 bool addrof;
4367
4368 if (TREE_CODE (base) == ADDR_EXPR)
4369 {
4370 base = TREE_OPERAND (base, 0);
4371 addrof = true;
4372 }
4373 else
4374 addrof = false;
4375 prev_base = base;
4376 base = get_addr_base_and_unit_offset (base, &base_offset);
4377 /* Aggregate arguments can have non-invariant addresses. */
4378 if (!base)
4379 {
4380 base = build_fold_addr_expr (prev_base);
4381 off = build_int_cst (adj->alias_ptr_type,
4382 adj->offset / BITS_PER_UNIT);
4383 }
4384 else if (TREE_CODE (base) == MEM_REF)
4385 {
4386 if (!addrof)
4387 {
4388 deref_base = true;
4389 deref_align = TYPE_ALIGN (TREE_TYPE (base));
4390 }
4391 off = build_int_cst (adj->alias_ptr_type,
4392 base_offset
4393 + adj->offset / BITS_PER_UNIT);
4394 off = int_const_binop (PLUS_EXPR, TREE_OPERAND (base, 1),
4395 off);
4396 base = TREE_OPERAND (base, 0);
4397 }
4398 else
4399 {
4400 off = build_int_cst (adj->alias_ptr_type,
4401 base_offset
4402 + adj->offset / BITS_PER_UNIT);
4403 base = build_fold_addr_expr (base);
4404 }
4405 }
4406
4407 if (!adj->by_ref)
4408 {
4409 tree type = adj->type;
4410 unsigned int align;
4411 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT misalign;
4412
4413 if (deref_base)
4414 {
4415 align = deref_align;
4416 misalign = 0;
4417 }
4418 else
4419 {
4420 get_pointer_alignment_1 (base, &align, &misalign);
4421 if (TYPE_ALIGN (type) > align)
4422 align = TYPE_ALIGN (type);
4423 }
4424 misalign += (offset_int::from (off, SIGNED).to_short_addr ()
4425 * BITS_PER_UNIT);
4426 misalign = misalign & (align - 1);
4427 if (misalign != 0)
4428 align = least_bit_hwi (misalign);
4429 if (align < TYPE_ALIGN (type))
4430 type = build_aligned_type (type, align);
4431 base = force_gimple_operand_gsi (&gsi, base,
4432 true, NULL, true, GSI_SAME_STMT);
4433 expr = fold_build2_loc (loc, MEM_REF, type, base, off);
4434 REF_REVERSE_STORAGE_ORDER (expr) = adj->reverse;
4435 /* If expr is not a valid gimple call argument emit
4436 a load into a temporary. */
4437 if (is_gimple_reg_type (TREE_TYPE (expr)))
4438 {
4439 gimple *tem = gimple_build_assign (NULL_TREE, expr);
4440 if (gimple_in_ssa_p (cfun))
4441 {
4442 gimple_set_vuse (tem, gimple_vuse (stmt));
4443 expr = make_ssa_name (TREE_TYPE (expr), tem);
4444 }
4445 else
4446 expr = create_tmp_reg (TREE_TYPE (expr));
4447 gimple_assign_set_lhs (tem, expr);
4448 gimple_set_location (tem, loc);
4449 gsi_insert_before (&gsi, tem, GSI_SAME_STMT);
4450 }
4451 }
4452 else
4453 {
4454 expr = fold_build2_loc (loc, MEM_REF, adj->type, base, off);
4455 REF_REVERSE_STORAGE_ORDER (expr) = adj->reverse;
4456 expr = build_fold_addr_expr (expr);
4457 expr = force_gimple_operand_gsi (&gsi, expr,
4458 true, NULL, true, GSI_SAME_STMT);
4459 }
4460 vargs.quick_push (expr);
4461 }
4462 if (adj->op != IPA_PARM_OP_COPY && MAY_HAVE_DEBUG_STMTS)
4463 {
4464 unsigned int ix;
4465 tree ddecl = NULL_TREE, origin = DECL_ORIGIN (adj->base), arg;
4466 gimple *def_temp;
4467
4468 arg = gimple_call_arg (stmt, adj->base_index);
4469 if (!useless_type_conversion_p (TREE_TYPE (origin), TREE_TYPE (arg)))
4470 {
4471 if (!fold_convertible_p (TREE_TYPE (origin), arg))
4472 continue;
4473 arg = fold_convert_loc (gimple_location (stmt),
4474 TREE_TYPE (origin), arg);
4475 }
4476 if (debug_args == NULL)
4477 debug_args = decl_debug_args_insert (callee_decl);
4478 for (ix = 0; vec_safe_iterate (*debug_args, ix, &ddecl); ix += 2)
4479 if (ddecl == origin)
4480 {
4481 ddecl = (**debug_args)[ix + 1];
4482 break;
4483 }
4484 if (ddecl == NULL)
4485 {
4486 ddecl = make_node (DEBUG_EXPR_DECL);
4487 DECL_ARTIFICIAL (ddecl) = 1;
4488 TREE_TYPE (ddecl) = TREE_TYPE (origin);
4489 SET_DECL_MODE (ddecl, DECL_MODE (origin));
4490
4491 vec_safe_push (*debug_args, origin);
4492 vec_safe_push (*debug_args, ddecl);
4493 }
4494 def_temp = gimple_build_debug_bind (ddecl, unshare_expr (arg), stmt);
4495 gsi_insert_before (&gsi, def_temp, GSI_SAME_STMT);
4496 }
4497 }
4498
4499 if (dump_file && (dump_flags & TDF_DETAILS))
4500 {
4501 fprintf (dump_file, "replacing stmt:");
4502 print_gimple_stmt (dump_file, gsi_stmt (gsi), 0, 0);
4503 }
4504
4505 new_stmt = gimple_build_call_vec (callee_decl, vargs);
4506 vargs.release ();
4507 if (gimple_call_lhs (stmt))
4508 gimple_call_set_lhs (new_stmt, gimple_call_lhs (stmt));
4509
4510 gimple_set_block (new_stmt, gimple_block (stmt));
4511 if (gimple_has_location (stmt))
4512 gimple_set_location (new_stmt, gimple_location (stmt));
4513 gimple_call_set_chain (new_stmt, gimple_call_chain (stmt));
4514 gimple_call_copy_flags (new_stmt, stmt);
4515 if (gimple_in_ssa_p (cfun))
4516 {
4517 gimple_set_vuse (new_stmt, gimple_vuse (stmt));
4518 if (gimple_vdef (stmt))
4519 {
4520 gimple_set_vdef (new_stmt, gimple_vdef (stmt));
4521 SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (gimple_vdef (new_stmt)) = new_stmt;
4522 }
4523 }
4524
4525 if (dump_file && (dump_flags & TDF_DETAILS))
4526 {
4527 fprintf (dump_file, "with stmt:");
4528 print_gimple_stmt (dump_file, new_stmt, 0, 0);
4529 fprintf (dump_file, "\n");
4530 }
4531 gsi_replace (&gsi, new_stmt, true);
4532 if (cs)
4533 cs->set_call_stmt (new_stmt);
4534 do
4535 {
4536 current_node->record_stmt_references (gsi_stmt (gsi));
4537 gsi_prev (&gsi);
4538 }
4539 while (gsi_stmt (gsi) != gsi_stmt (prev_gsi));
4540}
4541
4542/* If the expression *EXPR should be replaced by a reduction of a parameter, do
4543 so. ADJUSTMENTS is a pointer to a vector of adjustments. CONVERT
4544 specifies whether the function should care about type incompatibility the
4545 current and new expressions. If it is false, the function will leave
4546 incompatibility issues to the caller. Return true iff the expression
4547 was modified. */
4548
4549bool
4550ipa_modify_expr (tree *expr, bool convert,
4551 ipa_parm_adjustment_vec adjustments)
4552{
4553 struct ipa_parm_adjustment *cand
4554 = ipa_get_adjustment_candidate (&expr, &convert, adjustments, false);
4555 if (!cand)
4556 return false;
4557
4558 tree src;
4559 if (cand->by_ref)
4560 {
4561 src = build_simple_mem_ref (cand->new_decl);
4562 REF_REVERSE_STORAGE_ORDER (src) = cand->reverse;
4563 }
4564 else
4565 src = cand->new_decl;
4566
4567 if (dump_file && (dump_flags & TDF_DETAILS))
4568 {
4569 fprintf (dump_file, "About to replace expr ");
4570 print_generic_expr (dump_file, *expr, 0);
4571 fprintf (dump_file, " with ");
4572 print_generic_expr (dump_file, src, 0);
4573 fprintf (dump_file, "\n");
4574 }
4575
4576 if (convert && !useless_type_conversion_p (TREE_TYPE (*expr), cand->type))
4577 {
4578 tree vce = build1 (VIEW_CONVERT_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (*expr), src);
4579 *expr = vce;
4580 }
4581 else
4582 *expr = src;
4583 return true;
4584}
4585
4586/* If T is an SSA_NAME, return NULL if it is not a default def or
4587 return its base variable if it is. If IGNORE_DEFAULT_DEF is true,
4588 the base variable is always returned, regardless if it is a default
4589 def. Return T if it is not an SSA_NAME. */
4590
4591static tree
4592get_ssa_base_param (tree t, bool ignore_default_def)
4593{
4594 if (TREE_CODE (t) == SSA_NAME)
4595 {
4596 if (ignore_default_def || SSA_NAME_IS_DEFAULT_DEF (t))
4597 return SSA_NAME_VAR (t);
4598 else
4599 return NULL_TREE;
4600 }
4601 return t;
4602}
4603
4604/* Given an expression, return an adjustment entry specifying the
4605 transformation to be done on EXPR. If no suitable adjustment entry
4606 was found, returns NULL.
4607
4608 If IGNORE_DEFAULT_DEF is set, consider SSA_NAMEs which are not a
4609 default def, otherwise bail on them.
4610
4611 If CONVERT is non-NULL, this function will set *CONVERT if the
4612 expression provided is a component reference. ADJUSTMENTS is the
4613 adjustments vector. */
4614
4615ipa_parm_adjustment *
4616ipa_get_adjustment_candidate (tree **expr, bool *convert,
4617 ipa_parm_adjustment_vec adjustments,
4618 bool ignore_default_def)
4619{
4620 if (TREE_CODE (**expr) == BIT_FIELD_REF
4621 || TREE_CODE (**expr) == IMAGPART_EXPR
4622 || TREE_CODE (**expr) == REALPART_EXPR)
4623 {
4624 *expr = &TREE_OPERAND (**expr, 0);
4625 if (convert)
4626 *convert = true;
4627 }
4628
4629 HOST_WIDE_INT offset, size, max_size;
4630 bool reverse;
4631 tree base
4632 = get_ref_base_and_extent (**expr, &offset, &size, &max_size, &reverse);
4633 if (!base || size == -1 || max_size == -1)
4634 return NULL;
4635
4636 if (TREE_CODE (base) == MEM_REF)
4637 {
4638 offset += mem_ref_offset (base).to_short_addr () * BITS_PER_UNIT;
4639 base = TREE_OPERAND (base, 0);
4640 }
4641
4642 base = get_ssa_base_param (base, ignore_default_def);
4643 if (!base || TREE_CODE (base) != PARM_DECL)
4644 return NULL;
4645
4646 struct ipa_parm_adjustment *cand = NULL;
4647 unsigned int len = adjustments.length ();
4648 for (unsigned i = 0; i < len; i++)
4649 {
4650 struct ipa_parm_adjustment *adj = &adjustments[i];
4651
4652 if (adj->base == base
4653 && (adj->offset == offset || adj->op == IPA_PARM_OP_REMOVE))
4654 {
4655 cand = adj;
4656 break;
4657 }
4658 }
4659
4660 if (!cand || cand->op == IPA_PARM_OP_COPY || cand->op == IPA_PARM_OP_REMOVE)
4661 return NULL;
4662 return cand;
4663}
4664
4665/* Return true iff BASE_INDEX is in ADJUSTMENTS more than once. */
4666
4667static bool
4668index_in_adjustments_multiple_times_p (int base_index,
4669 ipa_parm_adjustment_vec adjustments)
4670{
4671 int i, len = adjustments.length ();
4672 bool one = false;
4673
4674 for (i = 0; i < len; i++)
4675 {
4676 struct ipa_parm_adjustment *adj;
4677 adj = &adjustments[i];
4678
4679 if (adj->base_index == base_index)
4680 {
4681 if (one)
4682 return true;
4683 else
4684 one = true;
4685 }
4686 }
4687 return false;
4688}

4690
4691/* Return adjustments that should have the same effect on function parameters
4692 and call arguments as if they were first changed according to adjustments in
4693 INNER and then by adjustments in OUTER. */
4694
4695ipa_parm_adjustment_vec
4696ipa_combine_adjustments (ipa_parm_adjustment_vec inner,
4697 ipa_parm_adjustment_vec outer)
4698{
4699 int i, outlen = outer.length ();
4700 int inlen = inner.length ();
4701 int removals = 0;
4702 ipa_parm_adjustment_vec adjustments, tmp;
4703
4704 tmp.create (inlen);
4705 for (i = 0; i < inlen; i++)
4706 {
4707 struct ipa_parm_adjustment *n;
4708 n = &inner[i];
4709
4710 if (n->op == IPA_PARM_OP_REMOVE)
4711 removals++;
4712 else
4713 {
4714 /* FIXME: Handling of new arguments are not implemented yet. */
4715 gcc_assert (n->op != IPA_PARM_OP_NEW);
4716 tmp.quick_push (*n);
4717 }
4718 }
4719
4720 adjustments.create (outlen + removals);
4721 for (i = 0; i < outlen; i++)
4722 {
4723 struct ipa_parm_adjustment r;
4724 struct ipa_parm_adjustment *out = &outer[i];
4725 struct ipa_parm_adjustment *in = &tmp[out->base_index];
4726
4727 memset (&r, 0, sizeof (r));
4728 gcc_assert (in->op != IPA_PARM_OP_REMOVE);
4729 if (out->op == IPA_PARM_OP_REMOVE)
4730 {
4731 if (!index_in_adjustments_multiple_times_p (in->base_index, tmp))
4732 {
4733 r.op = IPA_PARM_OP_REMOVE;
4734 adjustments.quick_push (r);
4735 }
4736 continue;
4737 }
4738 else
4739 {
4740 /* FIXME: Handling of new arguments are not implemented yet. */
4741 gcc_assert (out->op != IPA_PARM_OP_NEW);
4742 }
4743
4744 r.base_index = in->base_index;
4745 r.type = out->type;
4746
4747 /* FIXME: Create nonlocal value too. */
4748
4749 if (in->op == IPA_PARM_OP_COPY && out->op == IPA_PARM_OP_COPY)
4750 r.op = IPA_PARM_OP_COPY;
4751 else if (in->op == IPA_PARM_OP_COPY)
4752 r.offset = out->offset;
4753 else if (out->op == IPA_PARM_OP_COPY)
4754 r.offset = in->offset;
4755 else
4756 r.offset = in->offset + out->offset;
4757 adjustments.quick_push (r);
4758 }
4759
4760 for (i = 0; i < inlen; i++)
4761 {
4762 struct ipa_parm_adjustment *n = &inner[i];
4763
4764 if (n->op == IPA_PARM_OP_REMOVE)
4765 adjustments.quick_push (*n);
4766 }
4767
4768 tmp.release ();
4769 return adjustments;
4770}

4843/* Stream out jump function JUMP_FUNC to OB. */
4844
4845static void
4846ipa_write_jump_function (struct output_block *ob,
4847 struct ipa_jump_func *jump_func)
4848{
4849 struct ipa_agg_jf_item *item;
4850 struct bitpack_d bp;
4851 int i, count;
4852
4853 streamer_write_uhwi (ob, jump_func->type);
4854 switch (jump_func->type)
4855 {
4856 case IPA_JF_UNKNOWN:
4857 break;
4858 case IPA_JF_CONST:
4859 gcc_assert (
4860 EXPR_LOCATION (jump_func->value.constant.value) == UNKNOWN_LOCATION);
4861 stream_write_tree (ob, jump_func->value.constant.value, true);
4862 break;
4863 case IPA_JF_PASS_THROUGH:
4864 streamer_write_uhwi (ob, jump_func->value.pass_through.operation);
4865 if (jump_func->value.pass_through.operation == NOP_EXPR)
4866 {
4867 streamer_write_uhwi (ob, jump_func->value.pass_through.formal_id);
4868 bp = bitpack_create (ob->main_stream);
4869 bp_pack_value (&bp, jump_func->value.pass_through.agg_preserved, 1);
4870 streamer_write_bitpack (&bp);
4871 }
4872 else if (TREE_CODE_CLASS (jump_func->value.pass_through.operation)
4873 == tcc_unary)
4874 streamer_write_uhwi (ob, jump_func->value.pass_through.formal_id);
4875 else
4876 {
4877 stream_write_tree (ob, jump_func->value.pass_through.operand, true);
4878 streamer_write_uhwi (ob, jump_func->value.pass_through.formal_id);
4879 }
4880 break;
4881 case IPA_JF_ANCESTOR:
4882 streamer_write_uhwi (ob, jump_func->value.ancestor.offset);
4883 streamer_write_uhwi (ob, jump_func->value.ancestor.formal_id);
4884 bp = bitpack_create (ob->main_stream);
4885 bp_pack_value (&bp, jump_func->value.ancestor.agg_preserved, 1);
4886 streamer_write_bitpack (&bp);
4887 break;
4888 }
4889
4890 count = vec_safe_length (jump_func->agg.items);
4891 streamer_write_uhwi (ob, count);
4892 if (count)
4893 {
4894 bp = bitpack_create (ob->main_stream);
4895 bp_pack_value (&bp, jump_func->agg.by_ref, 1);
4896 streamer_write_bitpack (&bp);
4897 }
4898
4899 FOR_EACH_VEC_SAFE_ELT (jump_func->agg.items, i, item)
4900 {
4901 streamer_write_uhwi (ob, item->offset);
4902 stream_write_tree (ob, item->value, true);
4903 }
4904
4905 bp = bitpack_create (ob->main_stream);
4906 bp_pack_value (&bp, !!jump_func->bits, 1);
4907 streamer_write_bitpack (&bp);
4908 if (jump_func->bits)
4909 {
4910 streamer_write_widest_int (ob, jump_func->bits->value);
4911 streamer_write_widest_int (ob, jump_func->bits->mask);
4912 }
4913 bp_pack_value (&bp, !!jump_func->m_vr, 1);
4914 streamer_write_bitpack (&bp);
4915 if (jump_func->m_vr)
4916 {
4917 streamer_write_enum (ob->main_stream, value_rang_type,
4918 VR_LAST, jump_func->m_vr->type);
4919 stream_write_tree (ob, jump_func->m_vr->min, true);
4920 stream_write_tree (ob, jump_func->m_vr->max, true);
4921 }
4922}
4923
4924/* Read in jump function JUMP_FUNC from IB. */
4925
4926static void
4927ipa_read_jump_function (struct lto_input_block *ib,
4928 struct ipa_jump_func *jump_func,
4929 struct cgraph_edge *cs,
4930 struct data_in *data_in)
4931{
4932 enum jump_func_type jftype;
4933 enum tree_code operation;
4934 int i, count;
4935
4936 jftype = (enum jump_func_type) streamer_read_uhwi (ib);
4937 switch (jftype)
4938 {
4939 case IPA_JF_UNKNOWN:
4940 ipa_set_jf_unknown (jump_func);
4941 break;
4942 case IPA_JF_CONST:
4943 ipa_set_jf_constant (jump_func, stream_read_tree (ib, data_in), cs);
4944 break;
4945 case IPA_JF_PASS_THROUGH:
4946 operation = (enum tree_code) streamer_read_uhwi (ib);
4947 if (operation == NOP_EXPR)
4948 {
4949 int formal_id = streamer_read_uhwi (ib);
4950 struct bitpack_d bp = streamer_read_bitpack (ib);
4951 bool agg_preserved = bp_unpack_value (&bp, 1);
4952 ipa_set_jf_simple_pass_through (jump_func, formal_id, agg_preserved);
4953 }
4954 else if (TREE_CODE_CLASS (operation) == tcc_unary)
4955 {
4956 int formal_id = streamer_read_uhwi (ib);
4957 ipa_set_jf_unary_pass_through (jump_func, formal_id, operation);
4958 }
4959 else
4960 {
4961 tree operand = stream_read_tree (ib, data_in);
4962 int formal_id = streamer_read_uhwi (ib);
4963 ipa_set_jf_arith_pass_through (jump_func, formal_id, operand,
4964 operation);
4965 }
4966 break;
4967 case IPA_JF_ANCESTOR:
4968 {
4969 HOST_WIDE_INT offset = streamer_read_uhwi (ib);
4970 int formal_id = streamer_read_uhwi (ib);
4971 struct bitpack_d bp = streamer_read_bitpack (ib);
4972 bool agg_preserved = bp_unpack_value (&bp, 1);
4973 ipa_set_ancestor_jf (jump_func, offset, formal_id, agg_preserved);
4974 break;
4975 }
4976 }
4977
4978 count = streamer_read_uhwi (ib);
4979 vec_alloc (jump_func->agg.items, count);
4980 if (count)
4981 {
4982 struct bitpack_d bp = streamer_read_bitpack (ib);
4983 jump_func->agg.by_ref = bp_unpack_value (&bp, 1);
4984 }
4985 for (i = 0; i < count; i++)
4986 {
4987 struct ipa_agg_jf_item item;
4988 item.offset = streamer_read_uhwi (ib);
4989 item.value = stream_read_tree (ib, data_in);
4990 jump_func->agg.items->quick_push (item);
4991 }
4992
4993 struct bitpack_d bp = streamer_read_bitpack (ib);
4994 bool bits_known = bp_unpack_value (&bp, 1);
4995 if (bits_known)
4996 {
4997 widest_int value = streamer_read_widest_int (ib);
4998 widest_int mask = streamer_read_widest_int (ib);
4999 ipa_set_jfunc_bits (jump_func, value, mask);
5000 }
5001 else
5002 jump_func->bits = NULL;
5003
5004 struct bitpack_d vr_bp = streamer_read_bitpack (ib);
5005 bool vr_known = bp_unpack_value (&vr_bp, 1);
5006 if (vr_known)
5007 {
5008 enum value_range_type type = streamer_read_enum (ib, value_range_type,
5009 VR_LAST);
5010 tree min = stream_read_tree (ib, data_in);
5011 tree max = stream_read_tree (ib, data_in);
5012 ipa_set_jfunc_vr (jump_func, type, min, max);
5013 }
5014 else
5015 jump_func->m_vr = NULL;
5016}

5018/* Stream out parts of cgraph_indirect_call_info corresponding to CS that are
5019 relevant to indirect inlining to OB. */
5020
5021static void
5022ipa_write_indirect_edge_info (struct output_block *ob,
5023 struct cgraph_edge *cs)
5024{

5032 bp_pack_value (&bp, ii->member_ptr, 1);
5033 bp_pack_value (&bp, ii->by_ref, 1);

5046 ii->context.stream_out (ob);
5047 }

5080
5081/* Stream out NODE info to OB. */
5082
5083static void
5084ipa_write_node_info (struct output_block *ob, struct cgraph_node *node)
5085{
5086 int node_ref;
5087 lto_symtab_encoder_t encoder;
5088 struct ipa_node_params *info = IPA_NODE_REF (node);
5089 int j;
5090 struct cgraph_edge *e;
5091 struct bitpack_d bp;
5092
5093 encoder = ob->decl_state->symtab_node_encoder;
5094 node_ref = lto_symtab_encoder_encode (encoder, node);
5095 streamer_write_uhwi (ob, node_ref);
5096
5097 streamer_write_uhwi (ob, ipa_get_param_count (info));
5098 for (j = 0; j < ipa_get_param_count (info); j++)
5099 streamer_write_uhwi (ob, ipa_get_param_move_cost (info, j));
5100 bp = bitpack_create (ob->main_stream);
5101 gcc_assert (info->analysis_done
5102 || ipa_get_param_count (info) == 0);
5103 gcc_assert (!info->node_enqueued);
5104 gcc_assert (!info->ipcp_orig_node);
5105 for (j = 0; j < ipa_get_param_count (info); j++)
5106 bp_pack_value (&bp, ipa_is_param_used (info, j), 1);
5107 streamer_write_bitpack (&bp);
5108 for (j = 0; j < ipa_get_param_count (info); j++)
5109 {
5110 streamer_write_hwi (ob, ipa_get_controlled_uses (info, j));
5111 stream_write_tree (ob, ipa_get_type (info, j), true);
5112 }
5113 for (e = node->callees; e; e = e->next_callee)
5114 {
5115 struct ipa_edge_args *args = IPA_EDGE_REF (e);
5116
5117 streamer_write_uhwi (ob,
5118 ipa_get_cs_argument_count (args) * 2
5119 + (args->polymorphic_call_contexts != NULL));
5120 for (j = 0; j < ipa_get_cs_argument_count (args); j++)
5121 {
5122 ipa_write_jump_function (ob, ipa_get_ith_jump_func (args, j));
5123 if (args->polymorphic_call_contexts != NULL)
5124 ipa_get_ith_polymorhic_call_context (args, j)->stream_out (ob);
5125 }
5126 }
5127 for (e = node->indirect_calls; e; e = e->next_callee)
5128 {
5129 struct ipa_edge_args *args = IPA_EDGE_REF (e);
5130
5131 streamer_write_uhwi (ob,
5132 ipa_get_cs_argument_count (args) * 2
5133 + (args->polymorphic_call_contexts != NULL));
5134 for (j = 0; j < ipa_get_cs_argument_count (args); j++)
5135 {
5136 ipa_write_jump_function (ob, ipa_get_ith_jump_func (args, j));
5137 if (args->polymorphic_call_contexts != NULL)
5138 ipa_get_ith_polymorhic_call_context (args, j)->stream_out (ob);
5139 }
5140 ipa_write_indirect_edge_info (ob, e);
5141 }
5142}

5144/* Stream in NODE info from IB. */
5145
5146static void
5147ipa_read_node_info (struct lto_input_block *ib, struct cgraph_node *node,
5148 struct data_in *data_in)
5149{
5150 struct ipa_node_params *info = IPA_NODE_REF (node);
5151 int k;
5152 struct cgraph_edge *e;
5153 struct bitpack_d bp;
5154
5155 ipa_alloc_node_params (node, streamer_read_uhwi (ib));
5156
5157 for (k = 0; k < ipa_get_param_count (info); k++)
5158 (*info->descriptors)[k].move_cost = streamer_read_uhwi (ib);
5159
5160 bp = streamer_read_bitpack (ib);
5161 if (ipa_get_param_count (info) != 0)
5162 info->analysis_done = true;
5163 info->node_enqueued = false;
5164 for (k = 0; k < ipa_get_param_count (info); k++)
5165 ipa_set_param_used (info, k, bp_unpack_value (&bp, 1));
5166 for (k = 0; k < ipa_get_param_count (info); k++)
5167 {
5168 ipa_set_controlled_uses (info, k, streamer_read_hwi (ib));
5169 (*info->descriptors)[k].decl_or_type = stream_read_tree (ib, data_in);
5170 }
5171 for (e = node->callees; e; e = e->next_callee)
5172 {
5173 struct ipa_edge_args *args = IPA_EDGE_REF (e);
5174 int count = streamer_read_uhwi (ib);
5175 bool contexts_computed = count & 1;
5176 count /= 2;
5177
5178 if (!count)
5179 continue;
5180 vec_safe_grow_cleared (args->jump_functions, count);
5181 if (contexts_computed)
5182 vec_safe_grow_cleared (args->polymorphic_call_contexts, count);
5183
5184 for (k = 0; k < ipa_get_cs_argument_count (args); k++)
5185 {
5186 ipa_read_jump_function (ib, ipa_get_ith_jump_func (args, k), e,
5187 data_in);
5188 if (contexts_computed)
5189 ipa_get_ith_polymorhic_call_context (args, k)->stream_in (ib, data_in);
5190 }
5191 }
5192 for (e = node->indirect_calls; e; e = e->next_callee)
5193 {
5194 struct ipa_edge_args *args = IPA_EDGE_REF (e);
5195 int count = streamer_read_uhwi (ib);
5196 bool contexts_computed = count & 1;
5197 count /= 2;
5198
5199 if (count)
5200 {
5201 vec_safe_grow_cleared (args->jump_functions, count);
5202 if (contexts_computed)
5203 vec_safe_grow_cleared (args->polymorphic_call_contexts, count);
5204 for (k = 0; k < ipa_get_cs_argument_count (args); k++)
5205 {
5206 ipa_read_jump_function (ib, ipa_get_ith_jump_func (args, k), e,
5207 data_in);
5208 if (contexts_computed)
5209 ipa_get_ith_polymorhic_call_context (args, k)->stream_in (ib, data_in);
5210 }
5211 }
5212 ipa_read_indirect_edge_info (ib, data_in, e);
5213 }
5214}

5332
5333void
5334write_ipcp_transformation_info (output_block *ob, cgraph_node *node)
5335{
5336 int node_ref;
5337 unsigned int count = 0;
5338 lto_symtab_encoder_t encoder;
5339 struct ipa_agg_replacement_value *aggvals, *av;
5340
5341 aggvals = ipa_get_agg_replacements_for_node (node);
5342 encoder = ob->decl_state->symtab_node_encoder;
5343 node_ref = lto_symtab_encoder_encode (encoder, node);
5344 streamer_write_uhwi (ob, node_ref);
5345
5346 for (av = aggvals; av; av = av->next)
5347 count++;
5348 streamer_write_uhwi (ob, count);
5349
5350 for (av = aggvals; av; av = av->next)
5351 {
5352 struct bitpack_d bp;
5353
5354 streamer_write_uhwi (ob, av->offset);
5355 streamer_write_uhwi (ob, av->index);
5356 stream_write_tree (ob, av->value, true);
5357
5358 bp = bitpack_create (ob->main_stream);
5359 bp_pack_value (&bp, av->by_ref, 1);
5360 streamer_write_bitpack (&bp);
5361 }
5362
5363 ipcp_transformation_summary *ts = ipcp_get_transformation_summary (node);
5364 if (ts && vec_safe_length (ts->m_vr) > 0)
5365 {
5366 count = ts->m_vr->length ();
5367 streamer_write_uhwi (ob, count);
5368 for (unsigned i = 0; i < count; ++i)
5369 {
5370 struct bitpack_d bp;
5371 ipa_vr *parm_vr = &(*ts->m_vr)[i];
5372 bp = bitpack_create (ob->main_stream);
5373 bp_pack_value (&bp, parm_vr->known, 1);
5374 streamer_write_bitpack (&bp);
5375 if (parm_vr->known)
5376 {
5377 streamer_write_enum (ob->main_stream, value_rang_type,
5378 VR_LAST, parm_vr->type);
5379 streamer_write_wide_int (ob, parm_vr->min);
5380 streamer_write_wide_int (ob, parm_vr->max);
5381 }
5382 }
5383 }
5384 else
5385 streamer_write_uhwi (ob, 0);
5386
5387 if (ts && vec_safe_length (ts->bits) > 0)
5388 {
5389 count = ts->bits->length ();
5390 streamer_write_uhwi (ob, count);
5391
5392 for (unsigned i = 0; i < count; ++i)
5393 {
5394 const ipa_bits *bits_jfunc = (*ts->bits)[i];
5395 struct bitpack_d bp = bitpack_create (ob->main_stream);
5396 bp_pack_value (&bp, !!bits_jfunc, 1);
5397 streamer_write_bitpack (&bp);
5398 if (bits_jfunc)
5399 {
5400 streamer_write_widest_int (ob, bits_jfunc->value);
5401 streamer_write_widest_int (ob, bits_jfunc->mask);
5402 }
5403 }
5404 }
5405 else
5406 streamer_write_uhwi (ob, 0);
5407}

5409/* Stream in the aggregate value replacement chain for NODE from IB. */
5410
5411static void
5412read_ipcp_transformation_info (lto_input_block *ib, cgraph_node *node,
5413 data_in *data_in)
5414{
5415 struct ipa_agg_replacement_value *aggvals = NULL;
5416 unsigned int count, i;
5417
5418 count = streamer_read_uhwi (ib);
5419 for (i = 0; i <count; i++)
5420 {
5421 struct ipa_agg_replacement_value *av;
5422 struct bitpack_d bp;
5423
5424 av = ggc_alloc<ipa_agg_replacement_value> ();
5425 av->offset = streamer_read_uhwi (ib);
5426 av->index = streamer_read_uhwi (ib);
5427 av->value = stream_read_tree (ib, data_in);
5428 bp = streamer_read_bitpack (ib);
5429 av->by_ref = bp_unpack_value (&bp, 1);
5430 av->next = aggvals;
5431 aggvals = av;
5432 }
5433 ipa_set_node_agg_value_chain (node, aggvals);
5434
5435 count = streamer_read_uhwi (ib);
5436 if (count > 0)
5437 {
5438 ipcp_grow_transformations_if_necessary ();
5439
5440 ipcp_transformation_summary *ts = ipcp_get_transformation_summary (node);
5441 vec_safe_grow_cleared (ts->m_vr, count);
5442 for (i = 0; i < count; i++)
5443 {
5444 ipa_vr *parm_vr;
5445 parm_vr = &(*ts->m_vr)[i];
5446 struct bitpack_d bp;
5447 bp = streamer_read_bitpack (ib);
5448 parm_vr->known = bp_unpack_value (&bp, 1);
5449 if (parm_vr->known)
5450 {
5451 parm_vr->type = streamer_read_enum (ib, value_range_type,
5452 VR_LAST);
5453 parm_vr->min = streamer_read_wide_int (ib);
5454 parm_vr->max = streamer_read_wide_int (ib);
5455 }
5456 }
5457 }
5458 count = streamer_read_uhwi (ib);
5459 if (count > 0)
5460 {
5461 ipcp_grow_transformations_if_necessary ();
5462
5463 ipcp_transformation_summary *ts = ipcp_get_transformation_summary (node);
5464 vec_safe_grow_cleared (ts->bits, count);
5465
5466 for (i = 0; i < count; i++)
5467 {
5468 struct bitpack_d bp = streamer_read_bitpack (ib);
5469 bool known = bp_unpack_value (&bp, 1);
5470 if (known)
5471 {
5472 ipa_bits *bits
5473 = ipa_get_ipa_bits_for_value (streamer_read_widest_int (ib),
5474 streamer_read_widest_int (ib));
5475 (*ts->bits)[i] = bits;
5476 }
5477 }
5478 }
5479}

5579/* Adjust the aggregate replacements in AGGVAL to reflect parameters skipped in
5580 NODE. */
5581
5582static void
5583adjust_agg_replacement_values (struct cgraph_node *node,
5584 struct ipa_agg_replacement_value *aggval)
5585{
5586 struct ipa_agg_replacement_value *v;
5587 int i, c = 0, d = 0, *adj;
5588
5589 if (!node->clone.combined_args_to_skip)
5590 return;
5591
5592 for (v = aggval; v; v = v->next)
5593 {
5594 gcc_assert (v->index >= 0);
5595 if (c < v->index)
5596 c = v->index;
5597 }
5598 c++;
5599
5600 adj = XALLOCAVEC (int, c);
5601 for (i = 0; i < c; i++)
5602 if (bitmap_bit_p (node->clone.combined_args_to_skip, i))
5603 {
5604 adj[i] = -1;
5605 d++;
5606 }
5607 else
5608 adj[i] = i - d;
5609
5610 for (v = aggval; v; v = v->next)
5611 v->index = adj[v->index];
5612}
5613
5614/* Dominator walker driving the ipcp modification phase. */
5615
5616class ipcp_modif_dom_walker : public dom_walker
5617{
5618public:
5619 ipcp_modif_dom_walker (struct ipa_func_body_info *fbi,
5620 vec<ipa_param_descriptor, va_gc> *descs,
5621 struct ipa_agg_replacement_value *av,
5622 bool *sc, bool *cc)
5623 : dom_walker (CDI_DOMINATORS), m_fbi (fbi), m_descriptors (descs),
5624 m_aggval (av), m_something_changed (sc), m_cfg_changed (cc) {}
5625
5626 virtual edge before_dom_children (basic_block);
5627
5628private:
5629 struct ipa_func_body_info *m_fbi;
5630 vec<ipa_param_descriptor, va_gc> *m_descriptors;
5631 struct ipa_agg_replacement_value *m_aggval;
5632 bool *m_something_changed, *m_cfg_changed;
5633};
5634
5635edge
5636ipcp_modif_dom_walker::before_dom_children (basic_block bb)
5637{
5638 gimple_stmt_iterator gsi;
5639 for (gsi = gsi_start_bb (bb); !gsi_end_p (gsi); gsi_next (&gsi))
5640 {
5641 struct ipa_agg_replacement_value *v;
5642 gimple *stmt = gsi_stmt (gsi);
5643 tree rhs, val, t;
5644 HOST_WIDE_INT offset, size;
5645 int index;
5646 bool by_ref, vce;
5647
5648 if (!gimple_assign_load_p (stmt))
5649 continue;
5650 rhs = gimple_assign_rhs1 (stmt);
5651 if (!is_gimple_reg_type (TREE_TYPE (rhs)))
5652 continue;
5653
5654 vce = false;
5655 t = rhs;
5656 while (handled_component_p (t))
5657 {
5658 /* V_C_E can do things like convert an array of integers to one
5659 bigger integer and similar things we do not handle below. */
5660 if (TREE_CODE (rhs) == VIEW_CONVERT_EXPR)
5661 {
5662 vce = true;
5663 break;
5664 }
5665 t = TREE_OPERAND (t, 0);
5666 }
5667 if (vce)
5668 continue;
5669
5670 if (!ipa_load_from_parm_agg (m_fbi, m_descriptors, stmt, rhs, &index,
5671 &offset, &size, &by_ref))
5672 continue;
5673 for (v = m_aggval; v; v = v->next)
5674 if (v->index == index
5675 && v->offset == offset)
5676 break;
5677 if (!v
5678 || v->by_ref != by_ref
5679 || tree_to_shwi (TYPE_SIZE (TREE_TYPE (v->value))) != size)
5680 continue;
5681
5682 gcc_checking_assert (is_gimple_ip_invariant (v->value));
5683 if (!useless_type_conversion_p (TREE_TYPE (rhs), TREE_TYPE (v->value)))
5684 {
5685 if (fold_convertible_p (TREE_TYPE (rhs), v->value))
5686 val = fold_build1 (NOP_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (rhs), v->value);
5687 else if (TYPE_SIZE (TREE_TYPE (rhs))
5688 == TYPE_SIZE (TREE_TYPE (v->value)))
5689 val = fold_build1 (VIEW_CONVERT_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (rhs), v->value);
5690 else
5691 {
5692 if (dump_file)
5693 {
5694 fprintf (dump_file, " const ");
5695 print_generic_expr (dump_file, v->value, 0);
5696 fprintf (dump_file, " can't be converted to type of ");
5697 print_generic_expr (dump_file, rhs, 0);
5698 fprintf (dump_file, "\n");
5699 }
5700 continue;
5701 }
5702 }
5703 else
5704 val = v->value;
5705
5706 if (dump_file && (dump_flags & TDF_DETAILS))
5707 {
5708 fprintf (dump_file, "Modifying stmt:\n ");
5709 print_gimple_stmt (dump_file, stmt, 0, 0);
5710 }
5711 gimple_assign_set_rhs_from_tree (&gsi, val);
5712 update_stmt (stmt);
5713
5714 if (dump_file && (dump_flags & TDF_DETAILS))
5715 {
5716 fprintf (dump_file, "into:\n ");
5717 print_gimple_stmt (dump_file, stmt, 0, 0);
5718 fprintf (dump_file, "\n");
5719 }
5720
5721 *m_something_changed = true;
5722 if (maybe_clean_eh_stmt (stmt)
5723 && gimple_purge_dead_eh_edges (gimple_bb (stmt)))
5724 *m_cfg_changed = true;
5725 }
5726 return NULL;
5727}
5728
5729/* Update bits info of formal parameters as described in
5730 ipcp_transformation_summary. */
5731
5732static void
5733ipcp_update_bits (struct cgraph_node *node)
5734{
5735 tree parm = DECL_ARGUMENTS (node->decl);
5736 tree next_parm = parm;
5737 ipcp_transformation_summary *ts = ipcp_get_transformation_summary (node);
5738
5739 if (!ts || vec_safe_length (ts->bits) == 0)
5740 return;
5741
5742 vec<ipa_bits *, va_gc> &bits = *ts->bits;
5743 unsigned count = bits.length ();
5744
5745 for (unsigned i = 0; i < count; ++i, parm = next_parm)
5746 {
5747 if (node->clone.combined_args_to_skip
5748 && bitmap_bit_p (node->clone.combined_args_to_skip, i))
5749 continue;
5750
5751 gcc_checking_assert (parm);
5752 next_parm = DECL_CHAIN (parm);
5753
5754 if (!bits[i]
5755 || !(INTEGRAL_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (parm))
5756 || POINTER_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (parm)))
5757 || !is_gimple_reg (parm))
5758 continue;
5759
5760 tree ddef = ssa_default_def (DECL_STRUCT_FUNCTION (node->decl), parm);
5761 if (!ddef)
5762 continue;
5763
5764 if (dump_file)
5765 {
5766 fprintf (dump_file, "Adjusting mask for param %u to ", i);
5767 print_hex (bits[i]->mask, dump_file);
5768 fprintf (dump_file, "\n");
5769 }
5770
5771 if (INTEGRAL_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (ddef)))
5772 {
5773 unsigned prec = TYPE_PRECISION (TREE_TYPE (ddef));
5774 signop sgn = TYPE_SIGN (TREE_TYPE (ddef));
5775
5776 wide_int nonzero_bits = wide_int::from (bits[i]->mask, prec, UNSIGNED)
5777 | wide_int::from (bits[i]->value, prec, sgn);
5778 set_nonzero_bits (ddef, nonzero_bits);
5779 }
5780 else
5781 {
5782 unsigned tem = bits[i]->mask.to_uhwi ();
5783 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT bitpos = bits[i]->value.to_uhwi ();
5784 unsigned align = tem & -tem;
5785 unsigned misalign = bitpos & (align - 1);
5786
5787 if (align > 1)
5788 {
5789 if (dump_file)
5790 fprintf (dump_file, "Adjusting align: %u, misalign: %u\n", align, misalign);
5791
5792 unsigned old_align, old_misalign;
5793 struct ptr_info_def *pi = get_ptr_info (ddef);
5794 bool old_known = get_ptr_info_alignment (pi, &old_align, &old_misalign);
5795
5796 if (old_known
5797 && old_align > align)
5798 {
5799 if (dump_file)
5800 {
5801 fprintf (dump_file, "But alignment was already %u.\n", old_align);
5802 if ((old_misalign & (align - 1)) != misalign)
5803 fprintf (dump_file, "old_misalign (%u) and misalign (%u) mismatch\n",
5804 old_misalign, misalign);
5805 }
5806 continue;
5807 }
5808
5809 if (old_known
5810 && ((misalign & (old_align - 1)) != old_misalign)
5811 && dump_file)
5812 fprintf (dump_file, "old_misalign (%u) and misalign (%u) mismatch\n",
5813 old_misalign, misalign);
5814
5815 set_ptr_info_alignment (pi, align, misalign);
5816 }
5817 }
5818 }
5819}
5820
5821/* Update value range of formal parameters as described in
5822 ipcp_transformation_summary. */
5823
5824static void
5825ipcp_update_vr (struct cgraph_node *node)
5826{
5827 tree fndecl = node->decl;
5828 tree parm = DECL_ARGUMENTS (fndecl);
5829 tree next_parm = parm;
5830 ipcp_transformation_summary *ts = ipcp_get_transformation_summary (node);
5831 if (!ts || vec_safe_length (ts->m_vr) == 0)
5832 return;
5833 const vec<ipa_vr, va_gc> &vr = *ts->m_vr;
5834 unsigned count = vr.length ();
5835
5836 for (unsigned i = 0; i < count; ++i, parm = next_parm)
5837 {
5838 if (node->clone.combined_args_to_skip
5839 && bitmap_bit_p (node->clone.combined_args_to_skip, i))
5840 continue;
5841 gcc_checking_assert (parm);
5842 next_parm = DECL_CHAIN (parm);
5843 tree ddef = ssa_default_def (DECL_STRUCT_FUNCTION (node->decl), parm);
5844
5845 if (!ddef || !is_gimple_reg (parm))
5846 continue;
5847
5848 if (vr[i].known
5849 && (vr[i].type == VR_RANGE || vr[i].type == VR_ANTI_RANGE))
5850 {
5851 tree type = TREE_TYPE (ddef);
5852 unsigned prec = TYPE_PRECISION (type);
5853 if (INTEGRAL_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (ddef)))
5854 {
5855 if (dump_file)
5856 {
5857 fprintf (dump_file, "Setting value range of param %u ", i);
5858 fprintf (dump_file, "%s[",
5859 (vr[i].type == VR_ANTI_RANGE) ? "~" : "");
5860 print_decs (vr[i].min, dump_file);
5861 fprintf (dump_file, ", ");
5862 print_decs (vr[i].max, dump_file);
5863 fprintf (dump_file, "]\n");
5864 }
5865 set_range_info (ddef, vr[i].type,
5866 wide_int_storage::from (vr[i].min, prec,
5867 TYPE_SIGN (type)),
5868 wide_int_storage::from (vr[i].max, prec,
5869 TYPE_SIGN (type)));
5870 }
5871 else if (POINTER_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (ddef))
5872 && vr[i].type == VR_ANTI_RANGE
5873 && wi::eq_p (vr[i].min, 0)
5874 && wi::eq_p (vr[i].max, 0))
5875 {
5876 if (dump_file)
5877 fprintf (dump_file, "Setting nonnull for %u\n", i);
5878 set_ptr_nonnull (ddef);
5879 }
5880 }
5881 }
5882}
5883
5884/* IPCP transformation phase doing propagation of aggregate values. */
5885
5886unsigned int
5887ipcp_transform_function (struct cgraph_node *node)
5888{
5889 vec<ipa_param_descriptor, va_gc> *descriptors = NULL;
5890 struct ipa_func_body_info fbi;
5891 struct ipa_agg_replacement_value *aggval;
5892 int param_count;
5893 bool cfg_changed = false, something_changed = false;
5894
5895 gcc_checking_assert (cfun);
5896 gcc_checking_assert (current_function_decl);
5897
5898 if (dump_file)
5899 fprintf (dump_file, "Modification phase of node %s/%i\n",
5900 node->name (), node->order);
5901
5902 ipcp_update_bits (node);
5903 ipcp_update_vr (node);
5904 aggval = ipa_get_agg_replacements_for_node (node);
5905 if (!aggval)
5906 return 0;
5907 param_count = count_formal_params (node->decl);
5908 if (param_count == 0)
5909 return 0;
5910 adjust_agg_replacement_values (node, aggval);
5911 if (dump_file)
5912 ipa_dump_agg_replacement_values (dump_file, aggval);
5913
5914 fbi.node = node;
5915 fbi.info = NULL;
5916 fbi.bb_infos = vNULL;
5917 fbi.bb_infos.safe_grow_cleared (last_basic_block_for_fn (cfun));
5918 fbi.param_count = param_count;
5919 fbi.aa_walked = 0;
5920
5921 vec_safe_grow_cleared (descriptors, param_count);
5922 ipa_populate_param_decls (node, *descriptors);
5923 calculate_dominance_info (CDI_DOMINATORS);
5924 ipcp_modif_dom_walker (&fbi, descriptors, aggval, &something_changed,
5925 &cfg_changed).walk (ENTRY_BLOCK_PTR_FOR_FN (cfun));
5926
5927 int i;
5928 struct ipa_bb_info *bi;
5929 FOR_EACH_VEC_ELT (fbi.bb_infos, i, bi)
5930 free_ipa_bb_info (bi);
5931 fbi.bb_infos.release ();
5932 free_dominance_info (CDI_DOMINATORS);
5933 (*ipcp_transformations)[node->uid].agg_values = NULL;
5934 (*ipcp_transformations)[node->uid].bits = NULL;
5935 (*ipcp_transformations)[node->uid].m_vr = NULL;
5936
5937 vec_free (descriptors);
5938
5939 if (!something_changed)
5940 return 0;
5941 else if (cfg_changed)
5942 return TODO_update_ssa_only_virtuals | TODO_cleanup_cfg;
5943 else
5944 return TODO_update_ssa_only_virtuals;
5945}
